needed helper method are available in tqdm contrib logging for example tqdm implement a few trick to increase efficiency and reduce overhead avoid unnecessary frequent bar refreshing mininterval defines how long to wait between each refresh tqdm always get updated in the background but it will display only every mininterval reduce number of call to check system clock time mininterval is more intuitive to configure than miniters a clever adjustment system dynamic miniters will automatically adjust miniters to the amount of iteration that fit into time mininterval essentially tqdm will check if it s time to print without actually checking time this behaviour can be still be bypassed by manually setting miniters however consider a case with a combination of fast and slow iteration after a few fast iteration dynamic miniters will set miniters to a large number when iteration rate subsequently slows miniters will remain large and thus reduce display update frequency to address this maxinterval defines the maximum time between display refreshes a concurrent monitoring thread check for overdue update and force one where necessary the monitoring thread should not have a noticeable overhead and guarantee update at least every second by default this value can be directly changed by setting the monitor interval of any tqdm instance i e t tqdm tqdm t monitor interval the description: spacy is a library for advanced natural language processing in python and cython it s built on the very latest research and wa designed from day one to be used in real product spacy come with pretrained pipeline and currently support tokenization and training for language it feature state of the art speed and neural network model for tagging parsing named entity recognition text classification and more multi task learning with pretrained transformer like bert a well a a production ready training system and easy model packaging deployment and workflow management spacy is commercial open source software released under the mit license version out now check out the release note here the spacy project is maintained by the spacy team please understand that we won t be able to provide individual support via email we also believe that help is much more valuable if it s shared publicly so that more people can benefit from it for more detail see the fact figure and benchmark for detailed installation instruction see the documentation using pip spacy release are available a source package and binary wheel before you install spacy and it dependency make sure that your pip setuptools and wheel are up to date to install additional data table for lemmatization and normalization you can run pip install spacy lookup or install spacy lookup data separately the lookup package is needed to create blank model with lemmatization data and to lemmatize in language that don t yet come with pretrained model and aren t powered by third party library when using pip it is generally recommended to install package in a virtual environment to avoid modifying system state you can also install spacy from conda via the conda forge channel for the feedstock including the build recipe and configuration check out this repository some update to spacy may require downloading new statistical model if you re running spacy v or higher you can use the validate command to check if your installed model are compatible and if not print detail on how to update them if you ve trained your own model keep in mind that your training and runtime input must match after updating spacy we recommend retraining your model with the new version for detail on upgrading from spacy x to spacy x see the migration guide trained pipeline for spacy can be installed a python package this mean that they re a component of your application just like any other module model can be installed using spacy s download command or manually by pointing pip to a path or url to load a model use spacy load with the model name or a path to the model data directory you can also import a model directly via it full name and then call it load method with no argument for more info and example check out the model documentation the other way to install spacy is to clone it github repository and build it from source that is the common way if you want to make change to the code base you ll need to make sure that you have a development environment consisting of a python distribution including header file a compiler pip virtualenv and git installed the compiler part is the trickiest how to do that depends on your system for more detail and instruction see the documentation on compiling spacy from source and the quickstart widget to get the right command for your platform and python version to install with extra spacy come with an extensive test suite in order to run the test you ll usually want to clone the repository and build spacy from source this will also install the required development dependency and test utility defined in the requirement txt alternatively you can run pytest on the test from within the installed spacy package don t forget to also install the test utility via spacy s requirement txt

description: dill extends python s pickle module for serializing and de serializing python object to the majority of the built in python type serialization is the process of converting an object to a byte stream and the inverse of which is converting a byte stream back to a python object hierarchy dill provides the user the same interface a the pickle module and also includes some additional feature in addition to pickling python object dill provides the ability to save the state of an interpreter session in a single command hence it would be feasible to save an interpreter session close the interpreter ship the pickled file to another computer open a new interpreter unpickle the session and thus continue from the saved state of the original interpreter session dill can be used to store python object to a file but the primary usage is to send python object across the network a a byte stream dill is quite flexible and allows arbitrary user defined class and function to be serialized thus dill is not intended to be secure against erroneously or maliciously constructed data it is left to the user to decide whether the data they unpickle is from a trustworthy source dill is part of pathos a python framework for heterogeneous computing dill is in active development so any user feedback bug report comment or suggestion are highly appreciated a list of issue is located at http github com uqfoundation dill issue with a legacy list maintained at http uqfoundation github io project pathos query dill can pickle the following standard type none type bool int float complex byte str tuple list dict file buffer builtin python class namedtuples dataclasses metaclasses instance of class set frozenset array function exceptionsdill can also pickle more exotic standard type function with yield nested function lambda cell method unboundmethod module code methodwrapper methoddescriptor getsetdescriptor memberdescriptor wrapperdescriptor dictproxy slice notimplemented ellipsis quitdill cannot yet pickle these standard type frame generator tracebackdill also provides the capability to save and load python interpreter sessionssave and extract the source code from function and classesinteractively diagnose pickling errorsthe latest released version of dill is available from http pypi org project dilldill is distributed under a clause bsd license you can get the latest development version with all the shiny new feature at http github com uqfoundationif you have a new contribution please submit a pull request dill can be installed with pip to optionally include the objgraph diagnostic tool in the install for window user to optionally install session history tool dill requires python or pypy setuptools optional requirement objgraph pyreadline on window dill is a drop in replacement for pickle existing code can be updated to allow complete pickling using or dump convert the object to a unique byte string and load performs the inverse operation there are a number of option to control serialization which are provided a keyword argument to several dill function with protocol the pickle protocol level can be set this us the same value a the pickle module default protocol with byref true dill to behave a lot more like pickle with certain object like module pickled by reference a opposed to attempting to pickle the object itself with recurse true object referred to in the global dictionary are recursively traced and pickled instead of the default behavior of attempting to store the entire global dictionary with fmode the content of the file can be pickled along with the file handle which is useful if the object is being sent over the wire to a remote system which doe not have the original file on disk option are handle fmode for just the handle content fmode for the file content and file fmode for content and handle with ignore false object reconstructed with type defined in the top level script environment use the existing type in the environment rather than a possibly different reconstructed type the default serialization can also be set globally in dill setting thus we can modify how dill handle reference to the global dictionary locally or globally dill also includes source code inspection a an alternate to pickling to aid in debugging pickling issue use dill detect which provides tool like pickle tracing with trace we see how dill stored the lambda f by first storing create function the underlying code object co and create code which is used to handle code object then we handle the reference to the global dict d plus other dictionary d and d that save the lambda object s state a mark when the object is actually stored probably the best way to get started is to look at the documentation at http dill rtfd io also see dill test for a set of script that demonstrate how dill can serialize different python object you can run the test suite with python m dill test the content of any pickle file can be examined with undill a dill conforms to the pickle interface the example and documentation found at http doc python org library pickle html also apply to dill if one will import dill a pickle the source code is also generally well documented so further question may be resolved by inspecting the code itself please feel free to submit a ticket on github or ask a question on stackoverflow mike mckerns if you would like to share how you use dill in your work please send an email to mmckerns at uqfoundation dot org if you use dill to do research that lead to publication we ask that you acknowledge use of dill by citing the following in your publication please see http uqfoundation github io project pathos or http arxiv org pdf for further information

description: future is the missing compatibility layer between python and python it allows you to use a single clean python x compatible codebase to support both python and python with minimal overhead it is designed to be used a follows followed by predominantly standard idiomatic python code that then run similarly on python and python the import have no effect on python on python they shadow the corresponding builtins which normally have different semantics on python versus to provide their python semantics future support the standard library reorganization pep through the following py interface an included script called futurize aid in converting code from either python or python to code compatible with both platform it is similar to python modernize but go further in providing python compatibility through the use of the backported type and builtin function in future see http python future orged schofield jordan m adler et alpython charmer pty ltd australia and python charmer pte ltd singapore http pythoncharmers comsee doc credit rst or http python future org credit htmlcopyright python charmer pty ltd australia the software is distributed under an mit licence see license txt

description: pretty print tabular data in python a library and a command line utility the main use case of the library are to install the python library and the command line utility run the command line utility will be installed a tabulate to bin on linux e g usr bin or a tabulate exe to script in your python installation on window e g c python script tabulate exe you may consider installing the library only for the current user in this case the command line utility will be installed to local bin tabulate on linux and to appdata python script tabulate exe on window to install just the library on unix like operating system on window the module provides just one function tabulate which take a list of list or another tabular data type a the first argument and output a nicely formatted plain text table the following tabular data type are supported tabulate is a python library the second optional argument named header defines a list of column header to be used if header firstrow then the first row of data is used if header key then the key of a dictionary dataframe or column index are used it also work for numpy record array and list of dictionary or named tuples by default only panda dataframe table have an additional column called row index to add a similar column to any other type of table pas showindex always or showindex true argument to tabulate to suppress row index for all type of data pas showindex never or showindex false to add a custom row index column pas showindex rowids where rowids is some iterable there is more than one way to format a table in plain text the third optional argument named tablefmt defines how the table is formatted supported table format are plain table do not use any pseudo graphic to draw line simple is the default format the default may change in future version it corresponds to simple table in pandoc markdown extension github follows the convention of github flavored markdown it corresponds to the pipe format without alignment colon grid is like table formatted by emacs table el package it corresponds to grid table in pandoc markdown extension simple grid draw a grid using single line box drawing character rounded grid draw a grid using single line box drawing character with rounded corner heavy grid draw a grid using bold thick single line box drawing character mixed grid draw a grid using a mix of light thin and heavy thick line box drawing character double grid draw a grid using double line box drawing character fancy grid draw a grid using a mix of single and double line box drawing character outline is the same a the grid format but doesn t draw line between row simple outline is the same a the simple grid format but doesn t draw line between row rounded outline is the same a the rounded grid format but doesn t draw line between row heavy outline is the same a the heavy grid format but doesn t draw line between row mixed outline is the same a the mixed grid format but doesn t draw line between row double outline is the same a the double grid format but doesn t draw line between row fancy outline is the same a the fancy grid format but doesn t draw line between row presto is like table formatted by presto cli pretty attempt to be close to the format emitted by the prettytables library psql is like table formatted by postgres psql cli pipe follows the convention of php markdown extra extension it corresponds to pipe table in pandoc this format us colon to indicate column alignment asciidoc format data like a simple table of the asciidoctor format orgtbl follows the convention of emacs org mode and is editable also in the minor orgtbl mode hence it name jira follows the convention of atlassian jira markup language rst format data like a simple table of the restructuredtext format mediawiki format produce a table markup used in wikipedia and on other mediawiki based site moinmoin format produce a table markup used in moinmoin wikis youtrack format produce a table markup used in youtrack ticket textile format produce a table markup used in textile format html produce standard html markup a an html escape d str with a repr html method so that jupyter lab and notebook display the html and a str property so that the raw html remains accessible unsafehtml table format can be used if an unescaped html is required latex format creates a tabular environment for latex markup replacing special character like or to their latex correspondent latex raw behaves like latex but doe not escape latex command and special character latex booktabs creates a tabular environment for latex markup using spacing and style from the booktabs package latex longtable creates a table that can stretch along multiple page using the longtable package tabulate is smart about column alignment it detects column which contain only number and aligns them by a decimal point or flush them to the right if they appear to be integer text column are flushed to the left you can override the default alignment with numalign and stralign named argument possible column alignment are right center left decimal only for number and none to disable alignment aligning by a decimal point work best when you need to compare number at a glance compare this with a more common right alignment for tabulate anything which can be parsed a a number is a number even number represented a string are aligned properly this feature come in handy when reading a mixed table of text and number from a file to disable this feature use disable numparse true tabulate allows a custom column alignment to override the above the colalign argument can be a list or a tuple of stralign named argument possible column alignment are right center left decimal only for number and none to disable alignment omitting an alignment us the default for example tabulate allows to define custom number formatting applied to all column of decimal number use floatfmt named argument floatfmt argument can be a list or a tuple of format string one per column in which case every column may have different number formatting intfmt work similarly for integersby default tabulate remove leading and trailing whitespace from text column to disable whitespace removal set the global module level flag preserve whitespace to properly align table which contain wide character typically fullwidth glyph from chinese japanese or korean language the user should install wcwidth library to install it together with tabulate wide character support is enabled automatically if wcwidth library is already installed to disable wide character support without uninstalling wcwidth set the global module level flag wide char mode most table format support multiline cell text text containing newline character the newline character are honored a line break character multiline cell are supported for data row and for header row further automatic line break are not inserted of course some output format such a latex or html handle automatic formatting of the cell content on their own but for those that don t the newline character in the input cell text are the only mean to break a line in cell text note that some output format e g simple or plain do not represent row delimiters so that the representation of multiline cell in such format may be ambiguous to the reader the following example of formatted output use the following table with a multiline cell and header with a multiline cell plain table simple table grid table fancy grid table pipe table orgtbl table jira table presto table pretty table psql table rst table multiline cell are not well supported for the other table format while tabulate support data passed in with multilines entry explicitly provided it also provides some support to help manage this work internally the maxcolwidths argument is a list where each entry specifies the max width for it s respective column any cell that will exceed this will automatically wrap the content to assign the same max width for all column a singular int scaler can be used use none for any column where an explicit maximum doe not need to be provided and thus no automate multiline wrapping will take place the wrapping us the python standard textwrap wrap function with default parameter aside from width this example demonstrates usage of automatic multiline wrapping though typically the line being wrapped would probably be significantly longer than this one might want to add one or more separating line to highlight different section in a table the separating line will be of the same type a the one defined by the specified formatter a either the linebetweenrows linebelowheader linebelow lineabove or just a simple empty line when none is defined for the formatteransi escape code are non printable byte sequence usually used for terminal operation like setting color output or modifying cursor position because multi byte ansi sequence are inherently non printable they can still introduce unwanted extra length to string for example to deal with this string length are calculated after first removing all ansi escape sequence this ensures that the actual printable length is used for column width rather than the byte length in the final printable table however ansi escape sequence are not removed so the original styling is preserved some terminal support a special grouping of ansi escape sequence that are intended to display hyperlink much in the same way they are shown in browser these are handled just a mentioned before non printable ansi escape sequence are removed prior to string length calculation the only diifference with escaped hyperlink is that column width will be based on the length of the url text rather than the url itself terminal would show this text for example such feature a decimal point alignment and trying to parse everything a a number imply that tabulate it may not be suitable for serializing really big table but who s going to do that anyway or printing table in performance sensitive application tabulate is about two order of magnitude slower than simply joining list of value with a tab comma or other separator at the same time tabulate is comparable to other table pretty printer given a x table a list of list of mixed text and numeric data tabulate appears to be slower than asciitable and faster than prettytable and texttable the description: cloudpickle make it possible to serialize python construct not supported by the default pickle module from the python standard library cloudpickle is especially useful for cluster computing where python code is shipped over the network to execute on remote host possibly close to the data among other thing cloudpickle support pickling for lambda function along with function and class defined interactively in the main module for instance in a script a shell or a jupyter notebook cloudpickle can only be used to send object between the exact same version of python using cloudpickle for long term object storage is not supported and strongly discouraged security notice one should only load pickle data from trusted source a otherwise pickle load can lead to arbitrary code execution resulting in a critical security vulnerability the latest release of cloudpickle is available from pypi pickling a lambda expression pickling a function interactively defined in a python shell session in the main module an important difference between cloudpickle and pickle is that cloudpickle can serialize a function or class by value whereas pickle can only serialize it by reference serialization by reference treat function and class a attribute of module and pickle them through instruction that trigger the import of their module at load time serialization by reference is thus limited in that it assumes that the module containing the function or class is available importable in the unpickling environment this assumption break when pickling construct defined in an interactive session a case that is automatically detected by cloudpickle that pickle such construct by value another case where the importability assumption is expected to break is when developing a module in a distributed execution environment the worker process may not have access to the said module for example if they live on a different machine than the process in which the module is being developed by itself cloudpickle cannot detect such locally importable module and switch to serialization by value instead it relies on it default mode which is serialization by reference however since cloudpickle one can explicitly specify module for which serialization by value should be used using the register pickle by value module unregister pickle module api using this api there is no need to re install the new version of the module on all the worker node nor to restart the worker restarting the client python process with the new source code is enough note that this feature is still experimental and may fail in the following situation if the body of a function class pickled by value contains an import statement if a function pickled by reference us a function pickled by value description: stuart bishop stuart stuartbishop net pytz brings the olson tz database into python this library allows accurate and cross platform timezone calculation using python or higher it also solves the issue of ambiguous time at the end of daylight saving time which you can read more about in the python library reference datetime tzinfo almost all of the olson timezones are supported notethis library differs from the documented python api for tzinfo implementation if you want to create local wallclock time you need to use the localize method documented in this document in addition if you perform date arithmetic on local time that cross dst boundary the result may be in an incorrect timezone ie subtract minute from est and you get est instead of the correct edt a normalize method is provided to correct this unfortunately these issue cannot be resolved without modifying the python datetime implementation see pep this package can either be installed using pip or from a tarball using the standard python distutils if you are installing using pip you don t need to download anything a the latest version will be downloaded for you from pypi if you are installing from a tarball run the following command a an administrative user available a part of the tidelift subscription the maintainer of pytz and thousand of other package are working with tidelift to deliver commercial support and maintenance for the open source dependency you use to build your application save time reduce risk and improve code health while paying the maintainer of the exact dependency you use learn more this library only support two way of building a localized time the first is to use the localize method provided by the pytz library this is used to localize a naive datetime datetime with no timezone information the second way of building a localized time is by converting an existing localized time using the standard astimezone method unfortunately using the tzinfo argument of the standard datetime constructor doe not work with pytz for many timezones it is safe for timezones without daylight saving transition though such a utc the preferred way of dealing with time is to always work in utc converting to localtime only when generating output to be read by human this library also allows you to do date arithmetic using local time although it is more complicated than working in utc a you need to use the normalize method to handle daylight saving time and other timezone transition in this example loc dt is set to the instant when daylight saving time end in the u eastern timezone creating local time is also tricky and the reason why working with local time is not recommended unfortunately you cannot just pas a tzinfo argument when constructing a datetime see the next section for more detail converting between timezones is more easily done using the standard astimezone method you can take shortcut when dealing with the utc side of timezone conversion normalize and localize are not really necessary when there are no daylight saving time transition to deal with the tzinfo instance returned by the timezone function have been extended to cope with ambiguous time by adding an is dst parameter to the utcoffset dst tzname method the is dst parameter is ignored for most timestamps it is only used during dst transition ambiguous period to resolve that ambiguity if is dst is not specified ambiguous timestamps will raise an pytz exception ambiguoustimeerror exception the major problem we have to deal with is that certain datetimes may occur twice in a year for example in the u eastern timezone on the last sunday morning in october the following sequence happens edt occurs hour later instead of am the clock is turned back hour and happens again this time est in fact every instant between and occurs twice this mean that if you try and create a time in the u eastern timezone the standard datetime syntax there is no way to specify if you meant before of after the end of daylight saving time transition using the pytz custom syntax the best you can do is make an educated guess a you can see the system ha chosen one for you and there is a chance of it being out by one hour for some application this doe not matter however if you are trying to schedule meeting with people in different timezones or analyze log file it is not acceptable the best and simplest solution is to stick with using utc the pytz package encourages using utc for internal timezone representation by including a special utc implementation based on the standard python reference implementation in the python documentation the utc timezone unpickles to be the same instance and pickle to a smaller size than other pytz tzinfo instance the utc implementation can be obtained a pytz utc pytz utc or pytz timezone utc note that some other timezones are commonly thought of a the same gmt greenwich universal etc the definition of utc is distinct from these other timezones and they are not equivalent for this reason they will not compare the same in python see the section what is utc below if you insist on working with local time this library provides a facility for constructing them unambiguously if you pas none a the is dst flag to localize pytz will refuse to guess and raise exception if you try to build ambiguous or non existent time for example am on th oct happened twice in the u eastern timezone when the clock where put back at the end of daylight saving time similarly am on th april never happened at all in the u eastern timezone a the clock where put forward at am skipping the entire hour both of these exception share a common base class to make error handling easier a special case is where country change their timezone definition with no daylight saving time switch for example in warsaw switched from warsaw time to central european time with no daylight saving transition so at the stroke of midnight on august th the clock were wound back minute creating an ambiguous time period that cannot be specified without referring to the timezone abbreviation or the actual utc offset in this case midnight happened twice neither time during a daylight saving time period pytz handle this transition by treating the ambiguous period before the switch a daylight saving time and the ambiguous period after a standard time the best way of creating a time during an ambiguous time period is by converting from another timezone such a utc the standard python way of handling all these ambiguity is not to handle them such a demonstrated in this example using the u eastern timezone definition from the python documentation note that this implementation only work for date between and it is included for test only notice the first two result at first glance you might think they are correct but taking the utc offset into account you find that they are actually two hour appart instead of the hour we asked for a mechanism is provided to access the timezones commonly in use for a particular country looked up using the iso country code it return a list of string that can be used to retrieve the relevant tzinfo instance using pytz timezone the olson database come with a iso country code to english country name mapping that pytz expose a a dictionary utc is coordinated universal time it is a successor to but distinct from greenwich mean time gmt and the various definition of universal time utc is now the worldwide standard for regulating clock and time measurement all other timezones are defined relative to utc and include offset like utc hour to add or subtract from utc to derive the local time no daylight saving time occurs in utc making it a useful timezone to perform date arithmetic without worrying about the confusion and ambiguity caused by daylight saving time transition your country changing it timezone or mobile computer that roam through multiple timezones there are two list of timezones provided all timezones is the exhaustive list of the timezone name that can be used common timezones is a list of useful current timezones it doesn t contain deprecated zone or historical zone except for a few i ve deemed in common usage such a u eastern open a bug report if you think other timezones are deserving of being included here it is also a sequence of string both common timezones and all timezones are alphabetically sorted all timezones and common timezones are also available a set you can also retrieve list of timezones used by particular country using the country timezones function it requires an iso two letter country code pytz is an interface to the iana database which us ascii name the unicode consortium s unicode locale cldr project provides translation thomas khyn s l n package can be used to access these translation from python mit license this code is also available a part of zope under the zope public license version zpl i m happy to relicense this code if necessary for inclusion in other open source project this package will be updated after release of the olson timezone database the latest version can be downloaded from the python package index the code that is used to generate this distribution is hosted on launchpad net and available using git a mirror on github is also available at http github com stub pytzannouncements of new release are made on launchpad and the atom feed hosted there bug can be reported using launchpad bug report about security issue can be made via tidelift offset from utc are rounded to the nearest whole minute so timezones such a europe amsterdam pre will be up to second out this is a limitation of the python datetime library if you think a timezone definition is incorrect i probably can t fix it pytz is a direct translation of the olson timezone database and change to the timezone definition need to be made to this source if you find error they should be reported to the time zone mailing list linked from http www iana org time zone more info than you want to know about timezones http data iana org time zone tz link htmlstuart bishop stuart stuartbishop net

that class after declaring your attribute attrs give you a concise and explicit overview of the class s attribute a nice human readable repr equality checking method an initializer and much more without writing dull boilerplate code again and again and without runtime performance penalty hate type annotation no problem type are entirely optional with attrs simply assign attrs field to the attribute instead of annotating them with type this example us attrs s modern apis that have been introduced in version and the attrs package import name that ha been added in version the classic apis version to officially remove redis py requires a running redis server see redis s quickstart for installation instruction redis py can be installed using pip similar to other python package do not use sudo with pip it is usually good to work in a virtualenv or venv to avoid conflict with other package manager and python project for a quick introduction see python virtual environment in five minute to install redis py simply or from source view the current documentation here want to contribute a feature bug fix or report an issue check out our guide to contributing redis py support python by default all response are returned a byte in python if all string response from a client should be decoded the user can specify decode response true in redis init in this case any redis command that return a string type will be decoded with the encoding specified the default encoding is utf but this can be customized by specifying the encoding argument for the redis redis class the encoding will be used to automatically encode any string passed to command such a key name and value these command all accept a mapping of key value pair in redis py x this mapping could be specified a args or a kwargs both of these style caused issue when redis introduced optional flag to zadd relying on args caused issue with the optional argument order especially in python relying on kwargs caused potential collision issue of user key with the argument name in the method signature to resolve this redis py ha changed these three command to all accept a single positional argument named mapping that is expected to be a dict for mset and msetnx the dict is a mapping of key name value for zadd the dict is a mapping of element name score mset msetnx and zadd now look like all x user that use these command must modify their code to supply key and value a a dict to these command redis py x accidentally modified the argument order of zincrby swapping the order of value and amount zincrby now look like all x user that rely on zincrby must swap the order of amount and value for the command to continue to work a intended redis py only accepts user data a byte string or number ints longs and float attempting to specify a key or a value a any other type will raise a dataerror exception redis py x attempted to coerce any type of input into a string while occasionally convenient this caused all sort of hidden error when user passed boolean value which were coerced to true or false a none value which wa coerced to none or other value such a user defined type all x user should make sure that the key and value they pas into redis py are either byte string or number redis py drop support for the pipeline based lock and now only support the lua based lock in doing so lualock ha been renamed to lock this also mean that redis py lock object require redis server or greater x user that were explicitly referring to lualock will have to now refer to lock instead redis py now raise a lockerror when using a lock a a context manager and the lock cannot be acquired within the specified timeout this is more of a bug fix than a backwards incompatible change however given an error is now raised where none wa before this might alarm some user x user should make sure they re wrapping their lock code in a try catch like this the official redis command documentation doe a great job of explaining each command in detail redis py attempt to adhere to the official command syntax there are a few exception redis py drop support for the legacy redis client class strictredis ha been renamed to redis and an alias named strictredis is provided so that user previously using strictredis can continue to run unchanged the x redis class provided alternative implementation of a few command this confused user rightfully so and caused a number of support issue to make thing easier going forward it wa decided to drop support for these alternate implementation and instead focus on a single client class x user that are already using strictredis don t have to change the class name strictredis will continue to work for the foreseeable future x user that are using the redis class will have to make change if they use any of the following command behind the scene redis py us a connection pool to manage connection to a redis server by default each redis instance you create will in turn create it own connection pool you can override this behavior and use an existing connection pool by passing an already created connection pool instance to the connection pool argument of the redis class you may choose to do this in order to implement client side sharding or have fine grain control of how connection are managed connectionpools manage a set of connection instance redis py ship with two type of connection the default connection is a normal tcp socket based connection the unixdomainsocketconnection allows for client running on the same device a the server to connect via a unix domain socket to use a unixdomainsocketconnection connection simply pas the unix socket path argument which is a string to the unix domain socket file additionally make sure the unixsocket parameter is defined in your redis conf file it s commented out by default you can create your own connection subclass a well this may be useful if you want to control the socket behavior within an async framework to instantiate a client class using your own connection you need to create a connection pool passing your class to the connection class argument other keyword parameter you pas to the pool will be passed to the class specified during initialization connection maintain an open socket to the redis server sometimes these socket are interrupted or disconnected for a variety of reason for example network appliance load balancer and other service that sit between client and server are often configured to kill connection that remain idle for a given threshold when a connection becomes disconnected the next command issued on that connection will fail and redis py will raise a connectionerror to the caller this allows each application that us redis py to handle error in a way that s fitting for that specific application however constant error handling can be verbose and cumbersome especially when socket disconnection happen frequently in many production environment to combat this redis py can issue regular health check to ass the liveliness of a connection just before issuing a command user can pas health check interval n to the redis or connectionpool class or a a query argument within a redis url the value of health check interval must be an integer a value of the default disables health check any positive integer will enable health check health check are performed just before a command is executed if the underlying connection ha been idle for more than health check interval second for example health check interval will ensure that a health check is run on any connection that ha been idle for or more second just before a command is executed on that connection if your application is running in an environment that disconnect idle connection after second you should set the health check interval option to a value le than this option also work on any pubsub connection that is created from a client with health check interval enabled pubsub user need to ensure that get message or listen are called more frequently than health check interval second it is assumed that most workload already do this if your pubsub use case doesn t call get message or listen frequently you should call pubsub check health explicitly on a regularly basis redis py change the default value of the ssl cert reqs option from none to required see issue this change enforces hostname validation when accepting a cert from a remote ssl terminator if the terminator doesn t properly set the hostname on the cert this will cause redis py to raise a connectionerror this check can be disabled by setting ssl cert reqs to none note that doing so remove the security check do so at your own risk example with hostname verification using a local certificate bundle linux example with hostname verification using certifi example turning off hostname verification not recommended redis py can be used together with redis sentinel to discover redis node you need to have at least one sentinel daemon running in order to use redis py s sentinel support connecting redis py to the sentinel instance s is easy you can use a sentinel connection to discover the master and slave network address to connect to a sentinel which us ssl see ssl connection for more example of ssl configuration you can also create redis client connection from a sentinel instance you can connect to either the master for write operation or a slave for read only operation the master and slave object are normal redis instance with their connection pool bound to the sentinel instance when a sentinel backed client attempt to establish a connection it first query the sentinel server to determine an appropriate host to connect to if no server is found a masternotfounderror or slavenotfounderror is raised both exception are subclass of connectionerror when trying to connect to a slave client the sentinel connection pool will iterate over the list of slave until it find one that can be connected to if no slave can be connected to a connection will be established with the master see guideline for redis client with support for redis sentinel to learn more about redis sentinel parser class provide a way to control how response from the redis server are parsed redis py ship with two parser class the pythonparser and the hiredisparser by default redis py will attempt to use the hiredisparser if you have the hiredis module installed and will fallback to the pythonparser otherwise hiredis is a c library maintained by the core redis team pieter noordhuis wa kind enough to create python binding using hiredis can provide up to a x speed improvement in parsing response from the redis server the performance increase is most noticeable when retrieving many piece of data such a from lrange or smembers operation hiredis is available on pypi and can be installed via pip just like redis py the client class us a set of callback to cast redis response to the appropriate python type there are a number of these callback defined on the redis client class in a dictionary called response callback custom callback can be added on a per instance basis using the set response callback method this method accepts two argument a command name and the callback callback added in this manner are only valid on the instance the callback is added to if you want to define or override a callback globally you should make a subclass of the redis client and add your callback to it response callback class dictionary response callback take at least one parameter the response from the redis server keyword argument may also be accepted in order to further control how to interpret the response these keyword argument are specified during the command s call to execute command the zrange implementation demonstrates the use of response callback keyword argument with it withscores argument redis client instance can safely be shared between thread internally connection instance are only retrieved from the connection pool during command execution and returned to the pool directly after command execution never modifies state on the client instance however there is one caveat the redis select command the select command allows you to switch the database currently in use by the connection that database remains selected until another is selected or until the connection is closed this creates an issue in that connection could be returned to the pool that are connected to a different database a a result redis py doe not implement the select command on client instance if you use multiple redis database within the same application you should create a separate client instance and possibly a separate connection pool for each database it is not safe to pas pubsub or pipeline object between thread pipeline are a subclass of the base redis class that provide support for buffering multiple command to the server in a single request they can be used to dramatically increase the performance of group of command by reducing the number of back and forth tcp packet between the client and server pipeline are quite simple to use for ease of use all command being buffered into the pipeline return the pipeline object itself therefore call can be chained like in addition pipeline can also ensure the buffered command are executed atomically a a group this happens by default if you want to disable the atomic nature of a pipeline but still want to buffer command you can turn off transaction a common issue occurs when requiring atomic transaction but needing to implementation could get the value increment it in python and set the new value back however this is not atomic because multiple client could be doing this at the same time each getting the same value from get enter the watch command watch provides the ability to monitor one or more key prior to starting a transaction if any of those key change prior the execution of that transaction the entire like this which is much easier to read be sure to call pipe multi in the callable passed to redis transaction prior to any write command redis py includes a pubsub object that subscribes to channel and listens for new message creating a pubsub object is easy once a pubsub instance is created channel and pattern can be subscribed to the pubsub instance is now subscribed to those channel pattern the subscription confirmation can be seen by reading message from the pubsub instance every message read from a pubsub instance will be a dictionary with the following key let s send a message now unsubscribing work just like subscribing if no argument are passed to p unsubscribe all channel or pattern will be unsubscribed from redis py also allows you to register callback function to handle published message message handler take a single argument the message which is a dictionary just like the example above to subscribe to a channel or pattern with a message handler pas the channel or pattern name a a keyword argument with it value being the callback function when a message is read on a channel or pattern with a message handler the message dictionary is created and passed to the timeout the pubsub object will re subscribe to all prior channel and pattern when reconnecting message that were published while the client wa disconnected cannot be delivered when you re finished with a pubsub object call it close method to shutdown the connection the pubsub set of subcommands channel numsub and numpat are also supported redis py includes a monitor object that stream every create a script instance use the register script function on a client instance passing the lua code a the first argument register script return a script instance that you can use throughout your code result multiply is now a script instance that is invoked by calling it like a function script instance accept the following optional argument continuing the example from above the value of key foo is description: jsonpickle is a library for the two way conversion of complex python object and json jsonpickle build upon the existing json encoders such a simplejson json and ujson warningjsonpickle can execute arbitrary python code please see the security section for more detail for complete documentation please visit the jsonpickle documentation bug report and merge request are encouraged at the jsonpickle repository on github jsonpickle officially support cpython and cpython or greater version support below cpython will be dropped upon release of jsonpickle data serialized with python s pickle or cpickle or dill is not easily readable outside of python using the json format jsonpickle allows simple data type to be stored in a human readable format and more complex data type such a numpy array and panda dataframes to be machine readable on any platform that support json e g unlike pickled data jsonpickled data stored in an amazon s bucket is indexible by amazon s athena jsonpickle should be treated the same a the python stdlib pickle module from a security perspective warningthe jsonpickle module is not secure only unpickle data you trust it is possible to construct malicious pickle data which will execute arbitrary code during unpickling never unpickle data that could have come from an untrusted source or that could have been tampered with consider signing data with an hmac if you need to ensure that it ha not been tampered with safer deserialization approach such a reading json directly may be more appropriate if you are processing untrusted data install from pip for the latest stable release install from github for the latest change if you have the file checked out for development jsonpickle includes a built in numpy extension if would like to encode sklearn model numpy array and other numpy based data then you must enable the numpy extension by registering it handler jsonpickle includes a built in panda extension if would like to encode panda dataframe or series object then you must enable the panda extension by registering it handler jsonpicklejs is a javascript implementation of jsonpickle by michael scott cuthbert jsonpicklejs can be extremely useful for project that have parallel data structure between python and javascript licensed under the bsd license see copying for detail see jsonpicklejs license for detail about the jsonpicklejs license use make to run the unit test pytest is used to run unit test internally a tox target is provided to run test using tox setting multi test using all installed and supported python version jsonpickle itself ha no dependency beyond the python stdlib tox is required for testing when using the tox test runner only the testing requirement are specified in requirement dev txt it is recommended to create a virtualenv and run test from within the virtualenv or use a tool such a vx to activate the virtualenv without polluting the shell environment jsonpickle support multiple python version so using a combination of multiple virtualenvs and tox is useful in order to catch compatibility issue when developing

browse the documentation on the doc page the online documentation stay up to date with the development version of pygame on github this may be a bit newer than the version of pygame you are using to description: python dotenv read key value pair from a env file and can set them a environment variable it help in the development of application following the factor principle if your application take it configuration from environment variable like a factor application launching it in development is not very practical because you have to set those environment variable yourself to help you with that you can add python dotenv to your application to make it load the configuration from a env file when it is present e g in development while remaining configurable via the environment by default load dotenv doesn t override existing environment variable to configure the development environment add a env in the root directory of your project the syntax of env file supported by python dotenv is similar to that of bash if you use variable in value ensure they are surrounded with and like domain a bare variable such a domain are not expanded you will probably want to add env to your gitignore especially if it contains secret like a password see the section file format below for more information about what you can write in a env file the function dotenv value work more or le the same way a load dotenv except it doesn t touch the environment it just return a dict with the value parsed from the env file this notably enables advanced configuration management load dotenv and dotenv value accept stream via their stream argument it is thus possible to load the variable from source other than the filesystem e g the network you can use dotenv in ipython by default it will use find dotenv to search for a env file you can also specify a path optional flag a cli interface dotenv is also included which help you manipulate the env file without manually opening it run dotenv help for more information about the option and subcommands the format is not formally specified and still improves over time that being said env file should mostly look like bash file key can be unquoted or single quoted value can be unquoted single or double quoted space before and after key equal sign and value are ignored value can be followed by a comment line can start with the export directive which doe not affect their interpretation allowed escape sequence it is possible for single or double quoted value to span multiple line the following example are equivalent a variable can have no value it result in dotenv value associating that variable name with the value none e g foo none load dotenv on the other hand simply ignores such variable this shouldn t be confused with foo in which case the variable is associated with the empty string python dotenv can interpolate variable using posix variable expansion with load dotenv override true or dotenv value the value of a variable is the first of the value defined in the following list with load dotenv override false the value of a variable is the first of the value defined in the following list this project is currently maintained by saurabh kumar and bertrand bonnefoy claudet and would not have been possible without the support of these awesome people all notable change to this project will be documented in this file the format you expect notice that it ha the order this is because the list is being sorted in lexicographical order which sort number like you would letter i e b ba c natsort provides a function natsorted that help sort list naturally naturally is rather ill defined but in general it mean sorting based on meaning and not computer code point using natsorted is simple natsorted identifies number anywhere in a string and sort them naturally below are some other thing you can do with natsort also see the example for a quick start guide or the api for complete detail note natsorted is designed to be a drop in replacement for the built in sorted function like sorted natsorted doe not sort in place to sort a list and assign the output to the same variable you must explicitly assign the output to a variable please see generating a reusable sorting key and sorting in place for an alternate way to sort in place naturally sorting versionssort path like my file browser e g window explorer on window sorting by real number i e signed float locale aware sorting or human sorting further customizing natsortsorting mixed typeshandling bytesgenerating a reusable sorting key and sorting in placeother useful thingsnatsort doe not actually comprehend version number it just so happens that the most common versioning scheme are designed to work with standard natural sorting technique these scheme include major minor major minor patch year month day if your data conforms to a scheme like this then it will work out of the box with natsorted a of natsort version if you need to version that use a more complicated scheme please see these example prior to natsort version it wa a common request to be able to sort path like window explorer a of natsort the function o sorted ha been added to provide user the ability to sort in the order that their file browser might sort e g window explorer on window finder on macos dolphin nautilus thunar etc on linux output will be different depending on the operating system you are on for user not on window e g macos linux it is strongly recommended to also install pyicu which will help natsort give result that match most file browser if this is not installed it will fall back on python s built in locale module and will give good result for most input but will give poor result for special character this is useful in scientific data analysis and wa the default behavior of natsorted for natsort version use the realsorted function this is where the non numeric character are also ordered based on their meaning not on their ordinal value and a locale dependent thousand separator and decimal separator is accounted for in the number this can be achieved with the humansorted function you may find you need to explicitly set the locale to get this to work a shown in the example please see locale issue and the optional dependency section below before using the humansorted function if you need to combine multiple algorithm modifier such a n real n locale and n ignorecase you can combine the option using the bitwise or operator for example all of the available customizations can be found in the documentation for the n enum you can also add your own custom transformation function with the key argument these can be used with alg if you wish you can mix and match int float and str or unicode type when you sort natsort doe not officially support the byte type but convenience function are provided that help you decode to str first under the hood natsorted work by generating a custom sorting key using natsort keygen and then pass that to the built in sorted you can use the natsort keygen function yourself to generate a custom sorting key to sort in place using the list sort method all of the algorithm customizations mentioned in the further customizing natsort section can also be applied to natsort keygen through the alg keyword option recursively descend into list of listsautomatic unicode normalization of input datacontrolling the case sensitivitysorting file path correctlyallow custom sorting keysaccounting for unitsthe best way to debug natsorted is to generate a key using natsort keygen with the same option being passed to natsorted one can take a look at exactly what is being done with their input using this key it is highly recommended to look at this issue describing how to debug for how to debug and also to review the how doe natsort work page for why natsort is doing that to your data if you are trying to sort custom class and running into trouble please take a look at http github com sethmmorton natsort issue in short custom class are not likely to be sorted correctly if one relies on the behavior of lt and the other rich comparison operator in their custom class it is better to use a key function with natsort or use the natsort key a part of your rich comparison operator definition did you try to debug using the above advice if so and you still cannot figure out the error then please file an issue if you don t want to read how doe natsort work here is a quick primer natsort provides a key function that can be passed to list sort or sorted in order to modify the default sorting behavior this key is generated on demand with the key generator natsort natsort keygen natsort natsorted is essentially a wrapper for the following code user can further customize natsort sorting behavior with the key and or alg option see detail in the further customizing natsort section the key generated by natsort keygen always return a tuple it doe so in the following way some detail omitted for clarity assume the input is a string and attempt to split it into number and non number using regular expression number are then converted into either int or float if the above fails because the input is not a string assume the input is some other sequence e g list or tuple and recursively apply the key to each element of the sequence if the above fails because the input is not iterable assume the input is an int or float and just return the input in a tuple because a tuple is always returned a typeerror should not be common unless one try to do something odd like sort an int against a list natsort come with a shell script called natsort or can also be called from the command line with python m natsort natsort requires python or greater the most efficient sorting can occur if you install the fastnumbers package version it help with the string to number conversion natsort will still run efficiently without the package but if you need to squeeze out that extra juice it is recommended you include this a a dependency natsort will not require or check that fastnumbers is installed at installation it is recommended that you install pyicu if you wish to sort in a locale dependent manner see http natsort readthedocs io en master locale issue html for an explanation why use pip if you want to install the optional dependency you can use the extra notation at installation time to install those dependency a well use fast for fastnumbers and icu for pyicu please note that natsort is not set up to support python setup py test the recommended way to run test is with tox after installing tox running test is a simple a executing the following in the natsort directory tox will create virtual a virtual environment for your test and install all the needed testing requirement for you you can specify a particular python version with the e flag e g tox e py static analysis is done with tox e flake you can see all available testing environment with tox description: messagepack is an efficient binary serialization format it let you exchange data among multiple language like json but it s faster and smaller this package provides cpython binding for reading and writing messagepack data package name on pypi wa changed from msgpack python to msgpack from when upgrading from msgpack or earlier do pip uninstall msgpack python before pip install u msgpack you can use use bin type false option to pack byte object into raw type in the old msgpack spec instead of bin type in new msgpack spec you can unpack old msgpack format using raw true option it unpacks str raw type in msgpack into python byte see note below for detail python packerunpackerthe extension module in msgpack msgpack cmsgpack doe not support python and pypy but msgpack provides a pure python implementation msgpack fallback for pypy and python when you can t use a binary distribution you need to install visual studio or window sdk on window without extension using pure python implementation on cpython run slowly note in example below i use raw false and use bin type true for user using msgpack these option are default from msgpack so you can omit them use packb for packing and unpackb for unpacking msgpack provides dump and load a an alias for compatibility with json and pickle pack and dump pack to a file like object unpack and load unpacks from a file like object unpack unpacks msgpack s array to python s list but can also unpack to tuple you should always specify the use list keyword argument for backward compatibility see performance issue relating to use list option below read the docstring for other option unpacker is a streaming unpacker it unpacks multiple object from one stream or from byte provided through it feed method it is also possible to pack unpack custom data type here is an example for datetime datetime unpacker s object hook callback receives a dict the object pair hook callback may instead be used to receive a list of key value pair it is also possible to pack unpack custom data type using the ext type a an alternative to iteration unpacker object provide unpack skip read array header and read map header method the former two read an entire message from the stream respectively de serialising and returning the result or ignoring it the latter two method return the number of element in the upcoming container so that each element in an array or key value pair in a map can be unpacked or skipped individually early version of msgpack didn t distinguish string and binary type the type for representing both string and binary type wa named raw you can pack into and unpack from this old spec using use bin type false and raw true option to use the ext type pas msgpack exttype object to packer you can use it with default and ext hook see below to unpacking data received from unreliable source msgpack provides two security option max buffer size default limit the internal buffer size it is used to limit the preallocated list size too strict map key default true limit the type of map key to byte and str while msgpack spec doesn t limit the type of the map key there is a risk of the hashdos if you need to support other type for map key use strict map key false cpython s gc start when growing allocated object this mean unpacking may cause useless gc you can use gc disable when unpacking large message list is the default sequence type of python but tuple is lighter than list you can use use list false while unpacking when performance is important

description: the cvxpy documentation is at cvxpy org we are building a cvxpy community on discord join the conversation for issue and long form discussion use github issue and github discussion contentscvxpy is a python embedded modeling language for convex optimization problem it allows you to express your problem in a natural way that follows the math rather than in the restrictive standard form required by solver for example the following code solves a least square problem where the variable is constrained by lower and upper bound with cvxpy you can modelcvxpy is not a solver it relies upon the open source solver ecos sc and osqp additional solver are available but must be installed separately cvxpy began a a stanford university research project it is now developed by many people across many institution and country cvxpy is available on pypi and can be installed withcvxpy can also be installed with conda usingcvxpy ha the following dependency for detailed instruction see the installation guide to get started with cvxpy check out the following we encourage you to report issue using the github tracker we welcome all kind of issue especially those related to correctness documentation performance and feature request for basic usage question e g why isn t my problem dcp please use stackoverflow instead the cvxpy community consists of researcher data scientist software engineer and student from all over the world we welcome you to join u please be respectful in your communication with the cvxpy community and make sure to abide by our code of conduct we appreciate all contribution you don t need to be an expert in convex optimization to help out you should first install cvxpy from source here are some simple way to start contributing immediately if you d like to add a new example to our library or implement a new feature please get in touch with u first to make sure that your priority align with ours contribution should be submitted a pull request a member of the cvxpy development team will review the pull request and guide you through the contributing process before starting work on your contribution please read the contributing guide cvxpy is a community project built from the contribution of many researcher and engineer cvxpy is developed and maintained by steven diamond akshay agrawal riley murray and bartolomeo stellato with many others contributing significantly a non exhaustive list of people who have shaped cvxpy over the year includes stephen boyd eric chu robin verschueren michael sommerauer jaehyun park enzo busseti aj friend judson wilson chris dembia and philipp schiele for more information about the team and our process see our governance document if you use cvxpy for academic work we encourage you to cite our paper if you use cvxpy in industry we d love to hear from you a well on discord or over email

the server manager beware some post advise to install window server essential medium pack but this one requires the window server essential experience role and this role will deeply affect your window contains only opencv python package build script but not opencv itself python binding for opencv are developed in official opencv repository and it s the best place to report issue also please check opencv wiki http github com opencv opencv wiki and the official opencv forum before file new bug q why the package do not include non free algorithm a non free algorithm such a surf are not included in these package because they are patented non free and therefore cannot be distributed a built binary note that sift is included in the build due to patent expiration since opencv version and see this issue for more info http github com skvark opencv python issue q why the package and import are different opencv python v cv a it s easier for user to understand opencv python than cv and it make it easier to find the package with search engine cv old interface in old opencv version wa named a cv is the name that opencv developer chose when they created the binding generator this is kept a the import name to be consistent with different kind of tutorial around the internet changing the import name or behaviour would be also confusing to experienced user who are accustomed to the import cv the aim of this repository is to provide mean to package each new opencv release for the most used python version and platform the project is structured like a normal python package with a standard setup py file the build process for a single entry in the build matrix is a follows see for example github workflow build wheel linux yml file in linux and macos build get opencv s optional c description: the soundfile module is an audio library based on libsndfile cffi and numpy full documentation is available on http python soundfile readthedocs io the soundfile module can read and write sound file file reading writing is supported through libsndfile which is a free cross platform open source lgpl library for reading and writing many different sampled sound file format that run on many platform including window o x and unix it is accessed through cffi which is a foreign function interface for python calling c code cffi is supported for cpython x and pypy the soundfile module represents audio data a numpy array the soundfile module ha evolved rapidly during the last few release most notably we changed the import name from import pysoundfile to import soundfile in in we cleaned up many small inconsistency particularly in the the ordering and naming of function argument and the removal of the indexing interface in we changed the default value of always d from true to false also the order of argument of the write function changed from write data file to write file data in we changed the ctype argument of the buffer method to dtype using the numpy dtype notation the old ctype argument still work but are now officially deprecated the soundfile module depends on the python package cffi and numpy and the system library libsndfile in a modern python you can use pip install soundfile to download and install the latest release of the soundfile module and it dependency on window and o x this will also install the library libsndfile on linux you need to install libsndfile using your distribution s package manager for example sudo apt get install libsndfile if you are running on an unusual platform or if you are using an older version of python you might need to install numpy and cffi separately for example using the anaconda package manager or the unofficial window binary for python extension package in case of api usage error the soundfile module raise the usual valueerror or typeerror for other error soundfileerror is raised used to be runtimeerror particularly a libsndfileerror subclass of this exception is raised on error reported by the libsndfile library in that case the exception object provides the libsndfile internal error code in the libsndfileerror code attribute and the raw libsndfile error message in the libsndfileerror error string attribute data can be written to the file using soundfile write or read from the file using soundfile read the soundfile module can open all file format that libsndfile support for example wav flac ogg and mat file see known issue below about writing ogg file here is an example for a program that read a wave file and copy it into an flac file sound file can also be read in short optionally overlapping block with soundfile block for example this calculates the signal level for each block of a long file sound file can also be opened a soundfile object every soundfile ha a specific sample rate data format and a set number of channel if a file is opened it is kept open for a long a the soundfile object exists the file close when the object is garbage collected but you should use the soundfile close method or the context manager to close the file explicitly all data access us frame a index a frame is one discrete time step in the sound file every frame contains a many sample a there are channel in the file soundfile read can usually auto detect the file type of sound file this is not possible for raw file though note that on x this default to endian little if you are reading big endian data mostly old powerpc based file you have to set endian big accordingly you can write raw file in a similar way but be advised that in most case a more expressive format is better and should be used instead if you have an open file like object soundfile read can open it just like regular file here is an example using an http request note that the above example only work with description: inflect py correctly generate plural singular noun ordinal indefinite article convert number to word the method of the class engine in module inflect py provide plural inflection singular
