description: this package provides encoding and decoding routine that enable the serialization and deserialization of numerical and array data type provided by numpy using the highly efficient msgpack format serialization of python s native complex data type is also supported msgpack numpy requires msgpack python and numpy if you have pip installed on your system runto install the package and all dependency you can also download the source tarball unpack it and runfrom within the source directory the easiest way to use msgpack numpy is to call it monkey patching function after importing the python msgpack package this will automatically force all msgpack serialization and deserialization routine and other package that use them to become numpy aware of course one can also manually pas the encoder and decoder provided by msgpack numpy to the msgpack routine msgpack numpy will try to use the binary fast extension in msgpack by default if msgpack wa not compiled with cython or if the msgpack purepython variable is set it will fall back to using the slower pure python msgpack implementation the primary design goal of msgpack numpy is ensuring preservation of numerical data type during msgpack serialization and deserialization inclusion of type information in the serialized data necessarily incurs some storage overhead if preservation of type information is not needed one may be able to avoid some of this overhead by writing a custom encoder decoder pair that produce more efficient serialization for those specific use case numpy array with a dtype of o are serialized deserialized using pickle a a fallback solution to enable msgpack numpy to handle such array a the additional overhead of pickle serialization negates one of the reason to use msgpack it may be advisable to either write a custom encoder decoder to handle the specific use case efficiently or else not bother using msgpack numpy note that numpy array deserialized by msgpack numpy are read only and must be copied if they are to be modified the latest source code can be obtained from github msgpack numpy maintains compatibility with python version and install tox to support testing across multiple python version in your development environment if you use conda to install python use tox conda to automatically manage testing across all supported python version execute test across supported python version see the included author md file for more information this software is licensed under the bsd license see the included license md file for more information

description: pygtrie is a pure python implementation of a trie data structure compatible with python x and python x trie data structure also known a radix or prefix tree is a tree associating key to value where all the descendant of a node have a common prefix associated with that node the trie module contains trie chartrie and stringtrie class each implementing a mutable mapping interface i e dict interface a such in most circumstance trie could be used a a drop in replacement for a dict but the prefix nature of the data structure is trie s real strength the module also contains prefixset class which us a trie to store a set of prefix such that a key is contained in the set if it or it prefix is stored in the set a full mutable mapping implementation support iterating over a well a deleting a subtrie support prefix checking a well a shortest and longest prefix look up extensible for any kind of user defined key a prefixset support all key starting with given prefix logic can store any value including none to install pygtrie simply run or by adding line such a to project s requirement file alternatively if installation from source is desired it can be achieved by executing tbdadd pygtrie trie merge method which merges structure of two try add pygtrie trie strictly equal method which compare two try with stricter rule than regular equality operator it s not sufficient that key and value are the same but the structure of the try must be the same a well for example fix pygtrie trie eq implementation such that key value are taken into consideration rather than just looking at trie structure to see what this mean it s best to look at a few example firstly this used to be true since the two try have the same node structure however a far a mapping interface is concerned they use different key i e set t set t secondly this used to be false since the two try have different node structure the first one split key into foo bar baz while the second into foo bar baz however their key are the same i e set t set t and lastly this used to be true since the two try have the same node structure however the two class return key a different value pygtrie trie return key a tuples while pygtrie chartrie return them a string remove use of super in setup py to fix compatibility with python this change build code only no change to the library itself remove dependency on packaging module from setup py to fix installation on system without that package this change build code only no change to the library itself thanks to eric mclachlan for reporting pulled back from pypi change child argument of the node factory passed to pygtrie trie traverse from a generator to an iterator with a custom bool conversion this allows checking whether node ha child without having to iterate over them bool child to test whether this feature is available one can check whether trie traverse us bool convertible child property is true e g getattr pygtrie trie traverse us bool convertible child false thanks to pallab pain for suggesting the feature fix to attributeerror nochildren object ha no attribute sorted item failure when iterating over a trie with sorting enabled thanks to pallab pain for reporting add value property setter to step object returned by pygtrie trie walk towards et al this deprecates the set method the module now export pygtrie version making it possible to determine version of the library at run time trivial metadata fix pulled back from pypi fix to pygtrie prefixset initialisation incorrectly storing element even if their prefix are also added to the set for example prefixset foo foobar incorrectly resulted in a two element set even though the interface dictate that only foo is kept recall that if foo is member of the set foobar is a well thanks to tal maimon for reporting fix to pygtrie trie copy method not preserving enable sorting flag and in case of pygtrie stringtrie separator property add support for the copy module so copy copy can now be used with trie object leaf and node with just one child use more memory optimised representation which reduces overall memory usage of a trie structure minor performance improvement for adding new element to a pygtrie prefixset improvement to string representation of object which now includes type and for pygtrie stringtrie object value of separator property new pygtrie trie walk towards method allows walking a path towards a node with given key accessing each step of the path compared to pygtrie trie walk prefix method step for node without assigned value are returned fix to pygtrie prefixset copy not preserving type of backing trie pygtrie stringtrie now check and explicitly reject empty separator previously empty separator would be accepted but lead to confusing error later on thanks to waren long various documentation improvement python compatibility and test coverage python coverage report

description: the dateutil module provides powerful extension to the standard datetime module available in python dateutil can be installed from pypi using pip note that the package name is different on github http github com dateutil dateutil computing of relative delta next month next year next monday last week of month etc computing of relative delta between two given date and or datetime object computing of date based on very flexible recurrence rule using a superset of the icalendar specification parsing of rfc string is supported a well generic parsing of date in almost any string format timezone tzinfo implementation for tzfile format file etc localtime usr share zoneinfo etc tz environment string in all known format icalendar format file given range with help from relative delta local machine timezone fixed offset timezone utc timezone and window registry based time zone internal up to date world timezone information based on olson s database computing of easter sunday date for any given year using western orthodox or julian algorithm a comprehensive test suite here s a snapshot just to give an idea about the power of the package for more example look at the documentation suppose you want to know how much time is left in year month day etc before the next easter happening on a year with a friday th in august and you want to get today s date out of the description: the blosc development teamblosc blosc orghttps github com blosc python bloschttp python blosc blosc orgblosc http blosc org is a high performance compressor optimized for binary data it ha been designed to transmit data to the processor cache faster than the traditional non compressed direct memory fetch approach via a memcpy o call blosc work well for compressing numerical array that contains data with relatively low entropy like sparse data time series grid with regular spaced value etc python blosc a python package that wrap blosc python blosc support python or higher version blosc is now offering python wheel for the main o win mac and linux and platform you can install binary package from pypi using pip the sphinx based documentation is here http python blosc blosc orgalso some example are available on python blosc wiki page http github com blosc python blosc wikilastly here is the recording and the slide from the talk compress me stupid at the europython if you need more control there are different way to compile python blosc depending if you want to link with an already installed blosc library or not python blosc come with the blosc source with it and can be built with any codec can be enabled or disabled on this build path with the appropriate o environment variable include lz include snappy include zlib and include zlib by default all the codecs in blosc are enabled except snappy due to some issue with c with the gcc toolchain compiler specific optimisation are automatically enabled by inspecting the cpu flag building blosc they can be manually disabled by setting the following environmental variable disable blosc sse and disable blosc avx setuptools is limited to using the compiler specified in the environment variable cc which on posix system is usually gcc this often cause trouble with the snappy codec which is written in c and a a result snappy is no longer compiled by default this problem is not known to affect msvc or clang snappy is considered optional in blosc a it compression performance is below that of the other codecs that s all you can proceed with testing section now this approach us pre built fully optimized version of blosc built via cmake go to http github com blosc c blosc release and download and install the c blosc library then you can tell python blosc where is the c blosc library in a couple of way using an environment variable using flag after compiling you can quickly check that the package is sane by running the doctests in blosc test py or alternatively you can use the third party nosetests script once installed you can re run the test at any time with if curious you may want to run a small benchmark that compare a plain numpy array copy against compression through different compressor in your blosc build just to whet your appetite here are the result for an intel xeon e v ghz running python centos but ymmv and will vary also blosc work quite well on arm processor even without neon support yet for detail on the arm benchmark see http github com blosc python blosc issue in case you find your own result interesting please report them back to the author the software is license under a clause bsd licsense a copy of the python blosc license can be found in license txt a copy of all license can be found in license discussion about this module is welcome in the blosc list blosc googlegroups comhttp group google e group bloscenjoy data

description: pycryptodome is a self contained python package of low level cryptographic primitive it support python python and newer and pypy you can install it with all module are installed under the crypto package check the pycryptodomex project for the equivalent library that work under the cryptodome package pycryptodome is a fork of pycrypto it brings several enhancement with respect to the last official version of pycrypto for instance authenticated encryption mode gcm ccm eax siv ocb accelerated aes on intel platform via aes nifirst class support for pypyelliptic curve cryptography nist p curve ed ed better and more compact api nonce and iv attribute for cipher automatic generation of random nonce and iv simplified ctr cipher mode and more sha including shake xofs and blake hash algorithmssalsa and chacha stream ciphersscrypt and hkdfdeterministic ec dsa and eddsapassword protected pkcs key containersshamir s secret sharing schemerandom number get sourced directly from the o and not from a csprng in userspace simplified install process including better support for windowscleaner rsa and dsa key generation largely based on fips major clean ups and simplification of the code basepycryptodome is not a wrapper to a separate c library like openssl to the largest possible extent algorithm are implemented in pure python only the piece that are extremely critical to performance e g block cipher are implemented a c extension for more information see the homepage all the code can be downloaded from github

description: this package bundle some of the best python serialization library into one standalone package with a high level api that make it easy to write code that s correct across platform and python this allows u to provide all the serialization utility we need in a single binary wheel currently support json jsonl messagepack pickle and yaml serialization is hard especially across python version and multiple platform after dealing with many subtle bug over the year encoding locale large file our library like spacy and prodigy have steadily grown a number of utility function to wrap the multiple serialization format we need to support especially json msgpack and pickle these wrapping function ended up duplicated across our codebases so we wanted to put them in one place at the same time we noticed that having a lot of small dependency wa making maintenance harder and making installation slower to solve this we ve made srsly standalone by including the component package directly within it this way we can provide all the serialization utility we need in a single binary wheel srsly currently includes fork of the following package note that v x is only compatible with python for compatibility use v x srsly can be installed from pip before installing make sure that your pip setuptools and wheel are up to date or from conda via conda forge alternatively you can also compile the library from source you ll need to make sure that you have a development environment consisting of a python distribution including header file a compiler xcode command line tool on macos o x or visual c build tool on window pip virtualenv and git installed the underlying module is exposed via srsly ujson however we normally interact with it via the utility function only serialize an object to a json string fall back to json if sort key true is used until it s fixed in ujson deserialize unicode or byte to a python object create a json file and dump content or write to standard output load json from a file or standard input create a gzipped json file and dump content load gzipped json from a file create a jsonl file newline delimited json and dump content line by line or write to standard output read a jsonl file newline delimited json or from jsonl data from standard input and yield content line by line blank line will always be skipped check if a python object is json serializable the underlying module is exposed via srsly msgpack however we normally interact with it via the utility function only serialize an object to a msgpack byte string deserialize msgpack byte to a python object create a msgpack file and dump content load a msgpack file the underlying module is exposed via srsly cloudpickle however we normally interact with it via the utility function only serialize a python object with pickle deserialize byte with pickle the underlying module is exposed via srsly ruamel yaml however we normally interact with it via the utility function only serialize an object to a yaml string see the ruamel yaml doc for detail on the indentation format deserialize unicode or a file object to a python object create a yaml file and dump content or write to standard output load yaml from a file or standard input check if a python object is yaml serializable

description: this python package and extension are a number of tool for programming and manipulating the gdal geospatial data abstraction library actually it is two library gdal for manipulating geospatial raster data and ogr for manipulating geospatial vector data but we ll refer to the entire package a the gdal library for the purpose of this document the gdal project primarily even rouault maintains swig generated python binding for gdal and ogr generally speaking the class and method mostly match those of the gdal and ogr c class there is no python specific reference documentation but the gdal api tutorial includes python example libgdal or greater and header file gdal devel numpy or greater and header file numpy devel not explicitly required but many example and utility will not work without it gdal can be quite complex to build and install particularly on window and macos pre built binary are provided for the conda system http doc conda io en latest by the conda forge project http conda forge org once you have anaconda or miniconda installed you should be able to install gdal with conda install c conda forge gdalthe gdal python binding support both distutils and setuptools with a preference for using setuptools if setuptools can be imported setup will use that to build an egg by default if setuptools cannot be imported a simple distutils root install of the gdal package and no dependency chaining for numpy will be made gdal can be installed from the python package index pip install gdalit will be necessary to have libgdal and it development header installed if pip is expected to do a source build because no wheel is available for your specified platform and python version most of setup py s important variable are controlled with the setup cfg file in setup cfg you can modify pointer to include file and library the most important option that will likely need to be modified is the gdal config parameter if you installed gdal from a package the location of this program is likely usr bin gdal config but it may be in another place depending on how your packager arranged thing after modifying the location of gdal config you can build and install with the setup script if you have setuptools installed you can also generate an egg you can also have the gdal python binding built a part of a source build by specifying with python a part of your configure line use the typical make and make install command to complete the installation configure attempt to detect if you have setuptools installed in the tree of the python binary it wa given or detected on the execution path and it will use an egg build by default in that instance if you have a need to use a distutils only install you will have to edit setup py to ensure that the have setuptools variable is ultimately set to false and proceed with a typical python setup py install command you will need the following item to complete an install of the gdal python binding on window gdal window binary download the package that best match your environment a explained in the readme exe txt file after unzipping the gdal binary you will need to modify your system path and variable if you re not sure how to do this read the microsoft knowledge base docadd the installation directory bin folder to your system path remember to put a semicolon in front of it before you add to the existing path create a new user or system variable with the data folder from your installation skip down to the usage section to test your install note a reboot may be required the gdal python package is built using swig the earliest version of swig that is supported to generate the wrapper code is it is possible that usable binding will build with a version earlier than but no development effort are targeted at version below it you should not have to run swig in your development tree to generate the binding code a it is usually included with the source however if you do need to regenerate you can do so with the following make command from within the swig python directory to ensure that all of the binding are regenerated you can clean the binding code out before the generate command by issuing there are five major module that are included with the gdal python binding additionally there are five compatibility module that are included but provide notice to state that they are deprecated and will be going away if you are using gdal binding you should update your import to utilize the usage above but the following will work until gdal if you have previous code that imported the global module and still need to support the old import a simple try except import can silence the deprecation warning and keep thing named essentially the same a before currently only the ogr module ha docstrings which are generated from the c c api doxygen material some of the argument and type might not match up exactly with what you are seeing from python but they should be enough to get you going docstrings for gdal and osr are planned for a future release one advanced feature of the gdal python binding not found in the other language binding is integration with the python numerical array facility the gdal dataset readasarray method can be used to read raster data a numerical array ready to use with the python numerical array capability one example of gdal numpy integration is found in the val repl py script readasarray expects to make an entire copy of a raster band or dataset unless the data are explicitly subsetted a part of the function call for large data this approach is expected to be prohibitively memory intensive

description: ml collection is a library of python collection designed for ml use case the two class called configdict and frozenconfigdict are dict like data structure with dot access to nested element together they are supposed to be used a a main way of expressing configuration of experiment and model this document describes example usage of configdict frozenconfigdict fieldreference a frozenconfigdictis an immutable hashable type of configdict a fieldreference is useful for having multiple field use the same value it can also be used for lazy computation you can use placeholder a a shortcut to create a fieldreference field with a none default value this is useful if a program us optional configuration field note that the indirection provided by fieldreferences will be lost if accessed through a configdict using a fieldreference in a standard operation addition subtraction multiplication etc will return another fieldreference that point to the original s value you can use fieldreference get to execute the operation and get the reference s computed value and fieldreference set to change the original reference s value if a fieldreference ha none a it original value or any operation ha an argument of none then the lazy computation will evaluate to none we can also use field in a configdict in lazy computation in this case a field will only be lazily evaluated if configdict get ref is used to get it lazily computed value in a configdict can be overridden in the same way a regular value the reference to the fieldreference used for the lazy computation will be lost and all computation downstream in the reference graph will use the new value you cannot create cycle using reference fortunately the only way to create a cycle is by assigning a computed field to one that is not the result of computation this is forbidden here are some more advanced example showing lazy computation with different operator and data type you can use and eq a configdict to check equality among configdict and frozenconfigdict object equality check see if the computed value are the same equality is satisfied if two set of computation are different a long a they result in the same value here is an example with lock and deepcopy for more example take a look at ml collection config dict example for example and gotchas specifically about initializing a configdict see ml collection config dict example config dict initialization py this library add flag definition to absl flag to handle config file it doe not wrap absl flag so if using any standard flag definition alongside config file flag user must also import absl flag currently this module add two new flag type namely define config file which accepts a path to a python file that generates a configuration and define config dict which accepts a configuration directly configuration are dict like structure see configdict whose nested element can be overridden using special command line flag see the example below for more detail use ml collection config flag alongside absl flag for example script py config py now after running we get usage of define config dict is similar to define config file the main difference is the configuration is defined in script py instead of in a separate file script py config file flag are compatible with the command line flag syntax all the following option are supported for non boolean value in configuration option for boolean value are slightly different note that config boolean field value is not supported it s sometimes useful to be able to pas parameter into get config and change what is returned based on this configuration one example is if you are grid searching over parameter which have a different hierarchical structure the flag need to be present in the resulting configdict it would be possible to include the union of all possible leaf value in your configdict but this produce a confusing config result a you have to remember which parameter will actually have an effect and which won t a better system is to pas some configuration indicating which structure of configdict should be returned an example is the following config file the value of config string will be anything that is to the right of the first colon in the config file path if one exists if no colon exists no value is passed to get config producing a typeerror if get config expects a value the above example can be run like or like

description: pyautogui is a cross platform gui automation python module for human being used to programmatically control the mouse keyboard pip install pyautoguifull documentation available at http macos need the rubicon objc module installed in that order linux need the python xlib or python xlib for python module installed pillow need to be installed and on linux you may need to install additional library to make sure pillow s png jpeg work correctly see if you want to do development and contribute to pyautogui you will need to install these module from pypi the x y coordinate used by pyautogui ha the origin coordinate in the top left corner of the screen the x coordinate increase going to the right just a in mathematics but the y coordinate increase going down the opposite of mathematics on a screen that is x pixel in size coordinate are for the top left while is for the bottom right currently pyautogui only work on the primary monitor pyautogui isn t reliable for the description: pyasn is a python extension module that enables very fast ip address to autonomous system number lookup current state and historical lookup can be done based on the mrt rib bgp archive used a input pyasn is different from other asn lookup tool in that it provides offline and historical lookup it provides utility script for user to build their own lookup database based on any mrt rib archive this make pyasn much faster than online dig whois json lookup the module is written in c and python and cross compiles on linux and window underneath it us a radix tree data structure for storage of ip address in the current version it borrows code from py radix to support both ipv and ipv network prefix the current release is a beta compared to the previous version it provides support for python and add new functionality performance improvement and unit test pyasn is developed and maintained by researcher at the economics of cybersecurity research group at delft university of technology http econsec tbm tudlft nl the package is used on an almost daily basis and bug are fixed pretty quickly the package is largely developed and maintained by hadi asghari and arman noroozian please report any bug via github http github com hadiasghari pyasn or email the developer installation is a breeze via pip or with the standard python you will need to have pip setuptools and build essential installed if you build the package manually on ubuntu debian you can get them using the following command building the c module on window using either pip or from source requires microsoft visual c to be installed pyasn ha been tested using visual c express available freely from microsoft s website on both the official python release and miniconda other version of python visual studio and cygwin could also work with minor modification we plan to release pyasn package to major linux repository once it is out of beta a simple example that demonstrates most of the feature ipasn data file are a long list of prefix used to lookup a number for ip an excerpt from such a file look like this ipasn data file can be created by downloading mrt rib bgp archive from routeviews or similar source and parsing them using provided script that tail the bgp a path this can be done simply a follows note these script are by default installed to usr local bin and can be executed directly if you installed the package to a user directory these script will not be on the path and you will have to invoke them by navigating to the folder in which they have been copied e g local bin we also provide download link to a large number of previously generated ipasn data file these are based on weekly snapshot of the routeviews data from accessible here http data tu nl repository uuid d d b e b cb ad e new in v to save disk space you can gzip ipasn data file the load time will be slighlty longer initial loading of a ipasn data file is the most heavy operation of the package for fast lookup using multiple ipasn data file for instance for historical lookup on multiple date we recommend caching of loaded data file for better performance you can remove pyasn a follows if you built and installed the package your self use the recorded log to remove the installed file removing pyasn version pyasn v and v can be installed side by side due to lower cased package name to avoid mistake you can uninstall the old pyasn by deleting the following file from your python installation the main portion of the directory tree are a follows a limited number of unit test are provided in the test directory when downlading the source they can be run with the following command this beta release ha been tested under python version and to we appreciate contribution towards testing pyasn new in v pyasn util convert py offer a dump screen option which show the mrt rib archive content and the chosen origin a pyasn is licensed under the mit license it extends code from py radix michael j schultz and damien miller and improves upon it in several way for instance in lowering memory usage and adding bulk prefix origin load the underlying radix tree implementation is taken and modified from mrtd description: pint is a python package to define operate and manipulate physical quantity the product of a numerical value and a unit of measurement it allows arithmetic operation between them and conversion from and to different unit it is distributed with a comprehensive list of physical unit prefix and constant due to it modular design you can extend or even rewrite the complete list without changing the source code it support a lot of numpy mathematical operation without monkey patching or wrapping numpy it ha a complete test coverage it run in python with no other dependency it is licensed under bsd it is extremely easy and natural to use and you can make good use of numpy if you want to install pint simply or utilizing conda with the conda forge channel and then simply enjoy it full documentation is available at http pint readthedocs org a command line script pint convert provides a quick way to convert between unit or get conversion factor although there are already a few very good python package to handle physical quantity no one wa really fitting my need like most developer i programmed pint to scratch my own itch unit parsing prefixed and pluralized form of unit are recognized without explicitly defining them in other word a the prefix kilo and the unit meter are defined pint understands kilometer this result in a much shorter and maintainable unit definition list a compared to other package standalone unit definition unit definition are loaded from a text file which is simple and easy to edit adding and changing unit and their definition doe not involve changing the code advanced string formatting a quantity can be formatted into string using pep syntax extended conversion flag are given to provide symbolic latex and pretty formatting unit name translation is available if babel is installed free to choose the numerical type you can use any numerical type fraction float decimal numpy ndarray etc numpy is not required but supported awesome numpy integration when you choose to use a numpy ndarray it method and ufuncs are supported including automatic conversion of unit for example numpy arccos q will require a dimensionless q and the unit of the output quantity will be radian uncertainty integration transparently handle calculation with quantity with uncertainty like meter via the uncertainty package handle temperature conversion between unit with different reference point like position on a map or absolute temperature scale dependency free it depends only on python and it standard library it interacts with other package like numpy and uncertainty if they are installedpandas integration thanks to panda extension type it is now possible to use pint with panda operation on dataframes and between column are unit aware providing even more convenience for user of panda dataframes for full detail see the pint panda jupyter notebook pint is maintained by a community of scientist programmer and enthusiast around the world see author for a complete list to review an ordered list of notable change for each version of a project see change

description: prompt toolkit is a library for building powerful interactive command line application in python read the documentation on readthedocs please notice that this branch is the prompt toolkit branch for most user it should be compatible with prompt toolkit but it requires at least python on the plus side prompt toolkit is completely type annotated and us asyncio natively ptpython is an interactive python shell build on top of prompt toolkit more examplesprompt toolkit could be a replacement for gnu readline but it can be much more than that some feature pure python syntax highlighting of the input while typing for instance with a pygments lexer multi line input editing advanced code completion both emacs and vi key binding similar to readline even some advanced vi functionality like named register and digraph reverse and forward incremental search work well with unicode double width character chinese input selecting text for copy paste both emacs and vi style support for bracketed paste mouse support for cursor positioning and scrolling auto suggestion like fish shell multiple input buffer no global state lightweight the only dependency are pygments and wcwidth run on linux o x freebsd openbsd and window system and much more feel free to create ticket for bug and feature request and create pull request if you have nice patch that you would like to share with others for conda do prompt toolkit is cross platform and everything that you build on top should run fine on both unix and window system window support is best on recent window build for which the command line window support vt escape sequence if not supported we fall back to using win apis for color and cursor movement it s worth noting that the implementation is a best effort of what is possible both unix and window terminal have their limitation but in general the unix experience will still be a little better for window it s recommended to use either cmder or conemu the most simple example of the library would look like this for more complex example have a look in the example directory all example are chosen to demonstrate only one thing also don t be afraid to look at the source code the implementation of the prompt function could be a good start the source code of prompt toolkit should be readable concise and efficient we prefer short function focusing each on one task and for which the input and output type are clearly specified we mostly prefer composition over inheritance because inheritance can result in too much functionality in the same object we prefer immutable object where possible object don t change after initialization reusability is important we absolutely refrain from having a changing global state it should be possible to have multiple independent instance of the same code in the same process the architecture should be layered the lower level operate on primitive operation and data structure giving when correctly combined all the possible flexibility while at the higher level there should be a simpler api ready to use and sufficient for most use case thinking about algorithm and efficiency is important but avoid premature optimization pygments syntax highlighter wcwidth determine column needed for a wide character

description: noteas of sphinx the napoleon extension will come packaged with sphinx under sphinx ext napoleon the sphinxcontrib napoleon extension will continue to work with sphinx are you tired of writing docstrings that look like this restructuredtext is great but it creates visually dense hard to read docstrings compare the jumble above to the same thing rewritten according to the google python style guide much more legible no napoleon is a sphinx extension that enables sphinx to parse both numpy and google style docstrings the style recommended by khan academy napoleon is a pre processor that par numpy and google style docstrings and convert them to restructuredtext before sphinx attempt to parse them this happens in an intermediate step while sphinx is processing the documentation so it doesn t modify any of the docstrings in your actual source code file install the napoleon extension after setting up sphinx to build your doc enable napoleon in the sphinx conf py file use sphinx apidoc to build your api documentation napoleon interprets every docstring that sphinx autodoc can find including docstrings on module class attribute method function and variable inside each docstring specially formatted section are parsed and converted to restructuredtext all standard restructuredtext formatting still work a expected all of the following section header are supported args alias of parameter argument alias of parameter attributesexampleexampleskeyword args alias of keyword argument keyword argumentsmethodsnotenotesother parametersparametersreturn alias of return returnsraisesreferencessee alsowarningwarnings alias of warning warnsyield alias of yield yieldsnapoleon support two style of docstrings google and numpy the main difference between the two style is that google us indention to separate section whereas numpy us underline google style numpy style numpy style tends to require more vertical space whereas google style tends to use more horizontal space google style tends to be easier to read for short and simple docstrings whereas numpy style tends be easier to read for long and in depth docstrings the khan academy recommends using google style the choice between style is largely aesthetic but the two style should not be mixed choose one style for your project and be consistent with it for full documentation see http sphinxcontrib napoleon readthedocs io

description: a python library for accessing and searching dictionary via slashed path ala xpathbasically it let you glob over a dictionary a if it were a filesystem it allows you to specify glob ala the bash eglob syntax through some advanced fnmatch fnmatch magic to access dictionary element and provides some facility for filtering those result sdists are available on pypi http pypi python org pypi dpaththe best way to install dpath is via easy install or pip all of the function in this library except merge accept a separator argument which is the character that should separate path component the default is but you can set it to whatever you want suppose we have a dictionary like this and we want to ask a simple question like get me the value of the key in the b hash which is in the a hash that s easy or you could say give me a new dictionary with the value of all element in x a b where the key is equal to the glob cd okay sound easy wow that wa easy what if i want to iterate over the result and not get a merged view or what if i want to just get all the value back for the glob i don t care about the path they were found at let s use that same dictionary and set key like a b cd to the value waffle let s make a new key with the path a b e f g set it to roffle this behaves like mkdir p in that it make all the intermediate path necessary to get to the terminus this work the way we expect with list a well if you have a list object and set index of that list object it will grow the list object with none entry in order to make it big enough handy to delete key in an object use dpath util delete which accepts the same globbing syntax a the other method also check out dpath util merge the python dict update method is great and all but doesn t handle merging dictionary deeply this one doe now that s handy you shouldn t try to use this a a replacement for the deepcopy method however while merge doe create new dict and list object inside the target the terminus object string and ints are not copied they are just re referenced in the merged object all of the method in this library except new support a afilter argument this can be set to a function that will return true or false to say yes include that value in my result set or no don t include it filtering function receive every terminus node in a search e g anything that is not a dict or a list at the very end of the path for each value they return true to include that value in the result set or false to exclude it consider this example given the source dictionary we want to find all key inside it but we only really want the one that contain ffle in them obviously filtering function can perform more advanced test regular expression etc etc by default dpath only understands dictionary key that are integer or string string key must be non empty you can change this behavior by setting a library wide dpath option again by default this behavior is off and empty string key will result in dpath exception invalidkeyname being thrown the default behavior in dpath is to assume that the path given is a string which must be tokenized by splitting at the separator to yield a distinct set of path component against which dictionary key can be individually glob tested however this present a problem when you want to use path that have a separator in their name the tokenizer configure method and call self add subparser optionally to specify keyword argument e g help to the subparser collection call self add subparsers for example tap automatically handle all the following any type that can be instantiated with a string argument can be used for example inargs path is a path instance containing the string passed in through the command line each is automatically parsed to additionally booleans can be specified by prefix of true and false with any capitalization a well a or e g for true arg tru arg t arg all suffice these argument are parsed in exactly the same way a str int float and bool note bools can be specified using the same rule a above and that optional is equivalent to optional str if an argument arg is a list simply specify the value separated by space just a you would with regular argparse for example arg par to arg identical to list but parsed into a set rather than a list tuples can be used to specify a fixed number of argument with specified type using the syntax tuple type type etc e g tuple str int bool str tuples with a variable number of argument are specified by tuple type e g tuple int note tuple default to tuple str literal is analagous to argparse s choice which specifies the value that an argument can take for example if arg can only be one of h false or then you would specify that arg literal h false for instance arg false assigns arg to false and arg true throw error the literal type wa introduced in python pep and can be imported with from typing extension import literal union type must include the type keyword argument in add argument in order to specify which type to use a in the example below in python union type type etc can be replaced with type type etc but the type keyword argument must still be description: linux macoswindowswarningnetifaces need a new maintainer al tair is no longer able to maintain it or make new release due to work commitment it s been annoying me for some time that there s no easy way to get the address e of the machine s network interface from python there is a good reason for this difficulty which is that it is virtually impossible to do so in a portable manner however it seems to me that there should be a package you can easy install that will take care of working out the detail of doing so on the machine you re using then you can get on with writing python code without concerning yourself with the nitty gritty of system dependent low level networking apis this package attempt to solve that problem first you need to install it which you can do by typing note that you will need the relevant developer tool for your platform a netifaces is written in c and installing this way will compile the extension once that s done you ll need to start python and do something like the following then if you enteryou ll see the list of interface identifier for your machine you can ask for the address of a particular interface by doinghmmmm that result look a bit cryptic let s break it apart and explain what each piece mean it returned a dictionary so let s look there first each of the number refers to a particular address family in this case we have three address family listed on my system is af link which mean the link layer interface e g ethernet is af inet normal internet address and is af inet ipv but wait don t use these number in your code the numeric value here are system dependent fortunately i thought of that when writing netifaces so the module declares a range of value that you might need e g again on your system the number may be different so what we ve established is that the dictionary that s returned ha one entry for each address family for which this interface ha an address let s take a look at the af inet address now you might be wondering why this value is a list the reason is that it s possible for an interface to have more than one address even within the same family i ll say that again you can have more than one address of the same type associated with each interface asking for the address of a particular interface doesn t make sense right so we can see that this particular interface only ha one address and because it s a loopback interface it s point to point and therefore ha a peer address rather than a broadcast address let s look at a more interesting interface this interface ha two address see i told you both of them are regular ipv address although in one case the netmask ha been changed from it default the netmask may not appear on your system if it s set to the default for the address range because this interface isn t point to point it also ha broadcast address now say we want instead of the ip address to get the mac address that is the hardware address of the ethernet adapter running this interface we can donote that this may not be available on platform without getifaddrs unless they happen to implement siocgifhwaddr note also that you just get the address it s unlikely that you ll see anything else with an af link address oh and don t assume that all af link address are ethernet you might for instance be on a mac in which case no that isn t an exceptionally long ethernet mac address it s a firewire address a of version you can also obtain a list of gateway on your machine this dictionary is keyed on address family in this case af inet and each entry is a list of gateway a address interface is default tuples notice that here we have two separate gateway for ipv af inet some operating system support configuration like this and can either route packet based on their source or based on administratively configured routing table for convenience we also allow you to index the dictionary with the special value default which return a dictionary mapping address family to the default gateway in each case thus you can get the default ipv gateway withdo note that there may be no default gateway for any given address family this is currently very common for ipv and much le common for ipv but it can happen even for af inet btw if you re trying to configure your machine to have multiple gateway for the same address family it s a very good idea to check the documentation for your operating system very carefully a some system become extremely confused or route packet in a non obvious manner i m very interested in hearing from anyone on any platform for whom the gateway method doesn t produce the expected result it s quite complicated extracting this information from the operating system whichever operating system we re talking about and so i expect there s at least one system out there where this just won t work it get regular testing on o x linux and window it ha also been used successfully on solaris and it s expected to work properly on other unix like system a well if you are running something that is not supported and wish to contribute a patch please use github to send a pull request it s an mit style license see license because someone description: easily work with conll file using the familiar syntax of python homepagedocumentationas with most python package simply use pip to install from pypi pyconll is also available a a conda package on the pyconll channel only package and newer are available on conda at the moment pyconll support python and greater starting in version in general pyconll will focus development effort on officially supported python version python reached end of support in october this tool is intended to be a minimal low level expressive and pragmatic library in a widely used programming language pyconll creates a thin api on top of raw conll annotation that is simple and intuitive it offer the following feature regular ci testing and validation against all ud v x version a strong domain model that includes conll source sentence token tree etc a typed api for better development experience and better semantics a focus on usability and simplicity in design no dependency performance optimization for a smooth development workflow no matter the dataset size performs about faster than other comparable package see the following code example to understand the basic of the api a full definition of the api can be found in the documentation or use the quick start guide for a focused introduction this package edits conll u annotation this doe not include the annotated text itself word form on token are not editable and sentence token cannot be reassigned or reordered pyconll focus on editing conll u annotation rather than creating it or changing the underlying text that is annotated if there is interest in this functionality area please create a github issue for more visibility this package also is only validated against the conll u format the conll and conll x format are not supported but are very similar i originally intended to support these format a well but their format is not a well defined a conll u so they are not included please create an issue for visibility if this feature interest you lastly linguistic data can often be very large and this package attempt to keep that in mind pyconll provides method for creating in memory conll object along with an iterate only version in case a corpus is too large to store in memory the size of the memory structure is several time larger than the actual corpus file the iterate only version can parse upwards of word per second on a gb ram machine so for most datasets to be used on a local dev machine this package will perform well the release also improves parse time and memory footprint by about contribution to this project are welcome and encouraged if you are unsure how to contribute here is a guide from github explaining the basic workflow after cloning this repo please run pip install r requirement txt to properly setup locally some of these tool like yapf pylint and mypy do not have to be run locally but ci build will fail without their successful running some other release dependency like twine and sphinx are also installed for packaging new version use setuptools version or greater for creating the appropriate packaging that recognizes the python requires metadata final packaging and release is now done with github action so this is le of a concern when changing either of these file please change the markdown version and run make gendocs so that the other version stay in sync below enumerates the general release process explicitly this section is for internal use and most people do not have to worry about this first note that the dev branch is always a direct extension of master with the latest change since the last release that is it is essentially a staging release branch change the version in pyconll version py appropriately merge dev into master locally github doe not offer a fast forward merge and explicitly us no ff so to keep the linear nature of change merge locally to fast forward this is assuming that the dev branch look good on ci test which do not automatically run in this situation push the master branch this should start some ci test specifically for master after validating these result create a tag corresponding to the next version number and push the tag create a new release from this tag from the release page on creating this release two workflow will start one release to pypi and the other release to conda validate these workflow pas and the package is properly released on both platform

description: this is a python wrapper for ta lib based on cython instead of swig from the homepage ta lib is widely used by trading software developer requiring to perform technical analysis of financial market data the original python binding included with ta lib use swig which unfortunately are difficult to install and aren t a efficient a they could be therefore this project us cython and numpy to efficiently and cleanly bind to ta lib producing result time faster than the swig interface in addition this project also support the use of the polars and panda library you can install from pypi or checkout the source and run setup py yourself it also appears possible to install via conda forge to use ta lib for python you need to have the ta lib already installed you should probably follow their installation direction for your platform but some suggestion are included below for reference you can simply install using homebrew if you are using apple silicon such a the m processor and building mixed architecture homebrew project you might want to make sure it s being built for your architecture and perhaps you can set these before installing with pip you might also find this helpful particularly if you have tried several different installation without success download ta lib msvc zip and unzip to c ta lib this is a bit binary release if you want to use bit python you will need to build a bit version of the library some unofficial and unsupported instruction for building on bit window here for reference you might also try these unofficial window binary for both bit and bit http www lfd uci edu gohlke pythonlibs ta libdownload ta lib src tar gz and if you build ta lib using make jx it will fail but that s ok simply rerun make jx followed by sudo make install note if your directory path includes space the installation will probably fail with no such file or directory error if you get a warning that look like this this typically mean setup py can t find the underlying ta lib library a dependency which need to be installed if you installed the underlying ta lib library with a custom prefix e g with configure prefix prefix then when you go to install this python wrapper you can specify additional search path to find the library and include file for the underlying ta lib library using the ta library path and ta include path environment variable sometimes installation will produce build error like this or this typically mean that it can t find the underlying ta lib library a dependency which need to be installed on window this could be caused by installing the bit binary distribution of the underlying ta lib library but trying to use it with bit python sometimes installation will fail with error like this this typically mean that you need the python header and should run something like sometimes building the underlying ta lib library ha error running make that look like this this might mean that the directory path to the underlying ta lib library ha space in the directory name try putting it in a path that doe not have any space and trying again sometimes you might get this error running setup py this is likely an issue with trying to compile for bit platform but without the appropriate header you might find some success looking at the first answer to this question if you wonder why stochrsi give you different result than you expect probably you want stoch applied to rsi which is a little different than the stochrsi which is stochf applied to rsi if the build appears to hang you might be running on a vm with not enough memory try gb or gb similar to ta lib the function api provides a lightweight wrapper of the exposed ta lib indicator each function return an output array and have default value for their parameter unless specified a keyword argument typically these function will have an initial lookback period a required number of observation before an output is generated set to nan for convenience the function api support both numpy ndarray and panda series and polars series input all of the following example use the function api calculate a simple moving average of the close price calculating bollinger band with triple exponential moving average calculating momentum of the close price with a time period of the underlying ta lib c library handle nan s in a sometimes surprising manner by typically propagating nan s to the end of the output for example you can compare that to a panda rolling mean where their approach is to output nan until enough lookback value are observed to generate new output if you re already familiar with using the function api you should feel right at home using the abstract api every function take a collection of named input either a dict of numpy ndarray or panda series or polars series or a panda dataframe or polars dataframe if a panda dataframe or polars dataframe is provided the output is returned a the same type with named output column for example input could be provided for the typical ohlcv data function can either be imported directly or instantiated by name from there calling function is basically the same a the function api an experimental streaming api wa added that allows user to compute the latest value of an indicator this can be faster than using the function api for example in an application that receives streaming data and want to know just the most recent updated indicator value we can show all the ta function supported by ta lib either a a list or a a dict sorted by group e g overlap study momentum indicator etc

description: this package is in maintenance only mode new code should use the importlib metadata module in the python standard library to find and load entry point entry point are a way for python package to advertise object with some common interface the most common example are console script entry point which define shell command by identifying a python function to run group of entry point such a console script point to object with similar interface an application might use a group to find it plugins or multiple group if it ha different kind of plugins the entrypoints module contains function to find and load entry point you can install it from pypi with pip install entrypoints to advertise entry point when distributing a package see entry point in the python packaging user guide the pkg resource module distributed with setuptools provides a way to discover entrypoints a well but it contains other functionality unrelated to entrypoint discovery and it doe a lot of work at import time merely importing pkg resource cause it to scan the file of all installed package thus in environment where a large number of package are installed importing pkg resource can be very slow several second by contrast entrypoints is focused solely on entrypoint discovery and it is faster importing entrypoints doe not scan anything and getting a given entrypoint group performs a more focused scan when there are multiple version of the same distribution in different directory on sys path entrypoints follows the rule that the first one win in most case this follows the logic of import similarly entrypoints relies on pip to ensure that only one dist info or egg info directory exists for each installed package there is no reliable way to pick which of several dist info folder accurately relates to the importable module

description: gorilla is a python library that provides a convenient approach to monkey patching monkey patching is the process of modifying module and class attribute at runtime with the purpose of replacing or extending third party code although not a recommended practice it is sometimes useful to fix or modify the behaviour of a piece of code from a third party library or to extend it public interface while making the addition feel like they are built in into the library the python language make monkey patching extremely easy but the advantage of gorilla are multiple not only in assuring a consistent behaviour on both python and python version but also in preventing common source of error and making the process both intuitive and convenient even when faced with large number of patch to create intuitive and convenient decorator approach to create patch can create patch for all class or module member at once compatible with both python and python customizable behaviour thanks to the dynamic nature of python that make monkey patching possible the process happens at runtime without ever having to directly modify the source code of the third party library the code above creates two patch one for each member of the class myclass but doe not apply them yet in other word they define the information required to carry on the operation but are not yet inserted into the specified destination class destination class such patch created with the decorator can then be automatically retrieved by recursively scanning a package or a module then applied see the tutorial section from the documentation for more detailed example and explanation on how to use gorilla read the documentation online at gorilla readthedocs io or check it source in the doc directory project using gorilla include banamlflowchristopher crouzet christophercrouzet com

description: pre built cpu only opencv package for python check the manual build section if you wish to compile the binding from source to enable additional module such a cuda if you have previous other manually installed not installed via pip version of opencv installed e g cv module in the root of python s site package remove it before installation to avoid conflict make sure that your pip version is up to date is the minimum supported version pip install upgrade pip check version with pip v for example linux distribution ship usually with very old pip version which cause a lot of unexpected problem especially with the manylinux format select the correct package for your environment there are four different package see option and below and you should select only one of them do not install multiple different package in the same environment there is no plugin architecture all the package use the same namespace cv if you installed multiple different package in the same environment uninstall them all with pip uninstall and reinstall only one package a package for standard desktop environment window macos almost any gnu linux distribution b package for server headless environment such a docker cloud environment etc no gui library dependenciesthese package are smaller than the two other package above because they do not contain any gui functionality not compiled with qt other gui component this mean that the package avoid a heavy dependency chain to x library and you will have for example smaller docker image a a result you should always use these package if you do not use cv imshow et al or you are using some other package such a pyqt than opencv to create your gui import the package import cv all package contain haar cascade file cv data haarcascades can be used a a shortcut to the data folder for example cv cascadeclassifier cv data haarcascades haarcascade frontalface default xml read opencv documentationbefore opening a new issue read the faq below and have a look at the other issue which are already open q do i need to install also opencv separately a no the package are special wheel binary package and they already contain statically built opencv binary q pip install fails with modulenotfounderror no module named skbuild since opencv python version manylinux wheel were replaced by manylinux wheel if your pip is too old it will try to use the new source distribution introduced in to manually build opencv because it doe not know how to install manylinux wheel however source build will also fail because of too old pip because it doe not understand build dependency in pyproject toml to use the new manylinux pre built wheel or to build from source your pip version must be please upgrade pip with pip install upgrade pip q import fails on window importerror dll load failed the specified module could not be found a if the import fails on window make sure you have visual c redistributable installed if you are using older window version than window and latest system update are not installed universal c runtime might be also required window n and kn edition do not include medium feature pack which is required by opencv if you are using window n or kn edition please install also window medium feature pack if you have window server medium dlls are probably missing too please install the feature called medium foundation in the server manager beware some post advise to install window server essential medium pack but this one requires the window server essential experience role and this role will deeply affect your window server configuration by enforcing active directory integration etc so just installing the medium foundation should be a safer choice if the above doe not help check if you are using anaconda old anaconda version have a bug which cause the error see this issue for a manual fix if you still encounter the error after you have checked all the previous solution download dependency and open the cv pyd located usually at c user username appdata local program python pythonxx lib site package cv file with it to debug missing dll issue q i have some other import error a make sure you have removed old manual installation of opencv python binding cv so or cv pyd in site package q function foo or method bar return wrong result throw exception or crash interpreter what should i do a the repository contains only opencv python package build script but not opencv itself python binding for opencv are developed in official opencv repository and it s the best place to report issue also please check opencv wiki http github com opencv opencv wiki and the official opencv forum before file new bug q why the package do not include non free algorithm a non free algorithm such a surf are not included in these package because they are patented non free and therefore cannot be distributed a built binary note that sift is included in the build due to patent expiration since opencv version and see this issue for more info http github com skvark opencv python issue q why the package and import are different opencv python v cv a it s easier for user to understand opencv python than cv and it make it easier to find the package with search engine cv old interface in old opencv version wa named a cv is the name that opencv developer chose when they created the binding generator this is kept a the import name to be consistent with different kind of tutorial around the internet changing the import name or behaviour would be also confusing to experienced user who are accustomed to the import cv the aim of this repository is to provide mean to package each new opencv release for the most used python version and platform the project is structured like a normal python package with a standard setup py file the build process for a single entry in the build matrix is a follows see for example github workflow build wheel linux yml file in linux and macos build get opencv s optional c dependency that we compile againstcheckout repository and submodulesfind opencv version from the sourcesbuild opencvrearrange opencv s build result add our custom file and generate wheellinux and macos wheel are transformed with auditwheel and delocate correspondinglyinstall the generated wheeltest that python can import the library and run some sanity checksuse twine to upload the generated wheel to pypi only in release build step are handled by pip wheel the build can be customized with environment variable in addition to any variable that opencv s build accepts we recognize see the next section for more info about manual build outside the ci environment if some dependency is not enabled in the pre built wheel you can also run the build locally to create a custom wheel in order to build opencv python in an unoptimized debug build you need to side step the normal process a bit if you would like the build produce all compiler command then the following combination of flag and environment variable ha been tested to work on linux see this issue for more discussion http github com opencv opencv python issue since opencv version also source distribution are provided in pypi this mean that if your system is not compatible with any of the wheel in pypi pip will attempt to build opencv from source if you need a opencv version which is not available in pypi a a source distribution please follow the manual build guidance above instead of this one you can also force pip to build the wheel from the source distribution some example if you need contrib module or headless version just change the package name step in the previous section is not needed however any additional cmake flag can be provided via environment variable a described in step of the manual build section if none are provided opencv s cmake script will attempt to find and enable any suitable dependency headless distribution have hard coded cmake flag which disable all possible gui dependency on slow system such a raspberry pi the full build may take several hour on a core ryzen x the build take about minute opencv python package script in this repository is available under mit license opencv itself is available under apache license third party package license are at license rd party txt all wheel ship with ffmpeg licensed under the lgplv non headless linux wheel ship with qt licensed under the lgplv the package include also other binary full list of license can be found from license rd party txt find version py script search for the version information from opencv source and appends also a revision number specific to this repository to the version string it save the version information to version py file under cv in addition to some other flag a release is made and uploaded to pypi when a new tag is pushed to master branch these tag differentiate package this repo might have modification but opencv version stay same and should be incremented sequentially in practice release version number look like this cv major cv minor cv revision package revision e g the master branch follows opencv master branch release branch follows opencv bugfix release every commit to the master branch of this repo will be built possible build artifact use local version identifier cv major cv minor cv revision git hash of this repo e g a d these artifact can t be and will not be uploaded to pypi linux wheel are built using manylinux these wheel should work out of the box for most of the distros which use gnu c standard library out there since they are built against an old version of glibc the default manylinux image have been extended with some opencv dependency see docker folder for more info python x compatible pre built wheel are provided for the officially supported python version not in eol starting from and build the macos travis build environment wa updated to xcode the change effectively dropped support for older than macos version starting from and description: documentation python rust node j stackoverflow python rust node j user guide discord polars is a blazingly fast dataframes library implemented in rust using apache arrow columnar format a the memory model to learn more read the user guide polars is very fast in fact it is one of the best performing solution available see the result in h oai s db benchmark install the latest polars version with we also have a conda package conda install polars however pip is the preferred way to install polars you can also install the dependency directly release happen quite often weekly every few day at the moment so updating polars regularly to get the latest bugfixes feature might not be a bad idea you can take latest release from crate io or if you want to use the latest feature performance improvement point to the master branch of this repo required rust version want to know about all the feature polars support read the doc want to contribute read our contribution guideline if you want a bleeding edge release or maximal performance you should compile polars from source this can be done by going through the following step in sequence note that the rust crate implementing the python binding is called py polars to distinguish from the wrapped rust crate polars itself however both the python package and the python module are named polars so you can pip install polars and import polars polars ha transitioned to arrow arrow is a faster and safer implementation of the apache arrow columnar format arrow also ha a more granular code base helping to reduce the compiler bloat see this example do you expect more than billion row compile polars with the bigidx feature flag or for python user install pip install polars u idx don t use this unless you hit the row boundary a the default polars is faster and consumes le memory do you want polars to run on an old cpu e g dating from before install pip polars lts cpu this polars project is compiled without avx target feature development of polars is proudly powered by
