description: pywin is a lightweight python launcher and switcher for window command line and msys mingw it s similar to the py exe launcher switcher available in python but written with basic window batch script and a shell script for msys mingw support i use bash and command line shell tool from msysgit based on msys mingw to do most of my python development on window pywin support several useful feature defined in pep such a command line convention and hash bang python version header in source file while pywin lack some of py exe s feature it ha the basic and a few extra of it own window xp for command prompt supportwindows vista for msys mingw support requires mklink for symbolic link at least one installation of python up to though it s not useful without at least two easy install pip or gitmake sure the main python installation you want pywin to live under is in the path with multiple python installation it s recommended to have only the main and script directory from one installation in your path for example c python c python script pywin and it associated script are installed in the main directory of the active python version e g c there s no need to install it under more than one version of python if you do you ll have to run pywin genlaunchers for each version you install it under make sure that this main python directory is always on the path alternatively you can move the included script to another directory in your path pywin can create individual launch script to directly access core python installation e g python these can be called directly with or without argument from the window command prompt and msys mingw bash prompt to use this feature calllaunchers are created for all machine wide and user specific python installation found in the window registry window batch file will be added to the directory where pywin is located msys mingw relies on window link created programmatically with mklink which is why you must have window vista installed to make use of this project add a directive to the first or second line of a source file to have the correct interpreter called currently this only support python launcher created by the pywin genlaunchers command to use this feature you must associate the py extension with pywin bat using the included pyassoc utility note pywin command work from both window command line and msys mingw shell search for python installation and create batch file in the same directory where pywin is installed note if you re using msys mingw this must be run again in the msys mingw shell and you must have window vista set the default python to major minor version add the right python home directory and it associated script directory to the front of path remove any other existing reference to a python script directory in path examplepywin setdefault is only active for the current cmd exe or msys mingw shell session if you want to change the default python permanently you need to change your system or user path and make sure pywin is installed for that python version when calling this from msys mingw enter a dot first so the change to path propagate to your active shell e g pywin setdefault launch either a specific major minor version of python or a source file or both note that specifying a version of python on the command line will override any version in the header of the source file examplepywin will launch the first version of python found among any version specified after a in the first line of the source the interpreter will be invoked with any additional parameter example if the environment variable virtual env is set use that virtualenv s python exe if the environment variable pythonhome is set use it python exe if none of the above fall back to the first python exe found on the path with no argument pyassoc will register the py extension to run with pyhome pywin bat this change is made in the registry to hkey current user so that when py file are invoked any machine wide setting is overridden note that registry setting have no effect on launch py file under msys mingw original restore py registry setting to launch with pyhome python exeall user if administrator apply change to hkey local machine and remove any hkey current user python key note that user can override this with their own hkey current user value the variable pyhome used by pyassoc is set in this manner if the environment variable pythonhome is set use it if the environment variable defaultpython is set use it this is set when you call pywin setdefault version but only last for the current session the path the pyassoc bat script is in

description: homepage release changelogthe main part of the code issome contributed code is copyrighted by the contributor in these case that is indicated in the source file in question the python x library is released under lgpl v or later since see the file license for detail rc and before were released under gpl v the python x library requires python or newer it ha been tested to various extent with python and through the python x library will only work on system that have an x server installed such a most linux distros but will not work on window or macos the python xlib us the standard setuptools package to install run this command see the command help for detail python setup py install h alternatively you can run program from the distribution directory or change the module path in program there s a simple example program implemented twice using both the high level interface and the low level protocol the python x library is intended to be a fully functional x client library for python program it is written entirely in python in contrast to earlier x library for python the ancient x extension and the newer plxlib which were interface to the c xlib this is possible to do since x client program communicate with the x server via the x protocol the communication take place over tcp ip unix socket decnet or any other streaming network protocol the c xlib is merely an interface to this protocol providing function suitable for a c environment there are three advantage of implementing a pure python library integration the library can make use of the wonderful object system in python providing an easy to use class hierarchy portability the library will be usable on almost any computer which have python installed a c interface could be problematic to port to non unix system such a m window or openvms maintainability it is much easier to develop and debug native python module than module written in c the reference manual is not finished by far but is probably still useful it can be browsed online there are also some example program and of course the standard x documentation applies the low level protocol is complete implementing client side x r the high level object oriented interface is also fully functional it is possible to write client application with the library currently the only real application using python xlib is the window manager plwm starting with version there is a resource database implementation icccm support and a framework for adding x extension code several extension have been implemented record shape xinerama composite randr damage generic event security xfixes xinput xtest nv control dpms and xres patch for addition are very welcome there are most likely still bug but the library is at least stable enough to run plwm a continuously bigger part of the library is covered by regression test improving stability the documentation is still quite rudimentary but should be of some help for people programming with the xlib x beginner should first find some general text on x a very good starting point is http www rahul net kenton xsites htmlsee the file todo for a detailed list of what is missing approximately ordered by importance

description: new in source and test are compatible with python w o setup py setup py is now compatible with python a wellnew in multiple type or objectsnew in inspection and extension and thread safe method registrationthe simplegeneric module let you define simple single dispatch generic function akin to python s built in generic function like len iter and so on however instead of using specially named method these generic function use simple lookup table akin to those used by e g pickle dump and other generic function found in the python standard library a you can see from the above example generic function are actually quite common in python already but there is no standard way to create simple one this library attempt to fill that gap a generic function are an excellent alternative to the visitor pattern a well a being a great substitute for most common us of adaptation this library try to be the simplest possible implementation of generic function and it therefore eschews the use of multiple or predicate dispatch a well a avoiding speedup technique such a c dispatching or code generation but it ha absolutely no dependency other than python and the implementation is just a single python module of le than line defining and using a generic function is straightforward defining multiple method for the same type or object is an error and the when type decorator only accepts class or type method defined for supertypes are inherited following mro order classic class instance are also supported although the lookup process is slower than for new style instance a a convenience you can now pas more than one type or object to the registration method you can obtain a function s default implementation using it default attribute help and other documentation tool see generic function a normal function object with the same name attribute docstring and module a the prototype default function you can find out if a generic function ha a method for a type or object using the ha object and ha type method note that ha type only query whether there is a method registered for the exact type not subtypes or supertypes you can create a generic function that inherits from an existing generic function by calling generic on the existing function any method added to the new generic function override all method in the base function notice that even though move ha a method for type y the method defined for x in move take precedence this is because the move function is used a the default method of move and move ha no method for type y the first argument is always used for dispatching and it must always be passed positionally when the function is called documentation tool don t see the function s original argument signature so you have to describe it in the docstring if you have optional argument you must duplicate them on every method in order for them to work correctly on the plus side it mean you can have different default or required argument for each method although relying on that quirk probably isn t a good idea these restriction may be lifted in later release if i feel the need they would require runtime code generation the way i do it in ruledispatch however which is somewhat of a pain alternately i could use the bytecodeassembler package to do the code generation a that s a lot easier to use than string based code generation but that would introduce more dependency and i m trying to keep this simple so i can just toss it into chandler without a big footprint increase

package documentation is available at rtd for your convenience if you want to build the documentation from source do the developer installation a described above then run the following command from description: a reimplementation of the python standard library s itertools in python using picklable iterator object intended to be python and compatible also includes picklable python compatible implementation of some related utility including some function from the toolz library in picklable itertools extra because the standard library pickle module nor the excellent dill package can t serialize all of the itertools iterators at least on python at least some appear to be serializable on python because there are lot of instance where these thing in itertools would simplify code but can t be used because serializability must be maintained across both python and python the in development framework block is our first consumer we d like to be able to serialize the entire state of a long running program for later resumption we can t do this with non picklable object this should be a drop in replacement pretty self explanatory test against the standard library itertools or builtin implementation to verify behaviour match where python and python differ in their naming filterfalse v ifilterfalse zip longest v izip longest we provide both we also provide name that were only available in the python incarnation of itertools ifilter izip also available under their built in name in python filter zip for convenience a new object are added to the python itertools module we intend to add them accumulate for example appears only in python and a picklable implementation is contained in this package handle built in type gracefully if possible list iterators etc are not picklable on python x so we provide an alternative implementation file iterators are handled transparently a well dict iterators and set iterators are currently not supported picklable itertools xrange can be used a a drop in replacement for python xrange python range with the benefit that the iterators produced by it will be picklable on both python and premature optimization is the root of all evil these thing are implemented in python so speed is obviously not our primary concern several of the more advanced iterators are constructed by chaining simpler iterators together which is not the most efficient thing to do but simplifies the code a lot if it turn out that speed or a shallower object graph is necessary or desirable these can always be reimplemented pull request to this effect are welcome

description: welcome to the plyfile python module which provides a simple facility for reading and writing ascii and binary ply file the ply format is documented elsewhere plyfile may or may not work on older numpy version for example note that numpy before version ha a bug that break byte swapping by manipulating the byte order field of a plydata instance a a workaround you can manually byte swap your array using el data el data byteswap newbyteorder in addition to changing the byte order attribute quick way or clone the repository and run from the project root or just copy plyfile py into your gpl compatible project preferred more comprehensive requires tox and setuptools alternate requires py test and py both deserialization and serialization of ply file data is done through plydata and plyelement instance for the code example that follow assume the file tet ply contains the following text this file is available under the example directory orthe static method plydata read return a plydata instance which is plyfile s representation of the data in a ply file a plydata instance ha an attribute element which is a list of plyelement instance each of which ha a data attribute which is a numpy structured array containing the numerical data ply file element map onto numpy structured array in a pretty obvious way for a list property in an element the corresponding numpy field type is object with the member being numpy array see the vertex index example below concretely for convenience element and property can be looked up by name and element can be indexed directly without explicitly going through the data attribute the above expression is equivalent to plydata vertex data plyelement instance also contain metadata plyproperty and plylistproperty instance are used internally a a convenient intermediate representation of ply element property that can easily be serialized to a ply header using str or converted to numpy compatible type description via the dtype method it s not extremely common to manipulate them directly but if needed the property metadata of an element can be accessed a a tuple via the property attribute a illustrated above or looked up by name many but not necessarily all type of malformed input file will raise plyparseerror when plydata read is called the string value of the plyparseerror instance a well a attribute element row and prop provides additional context for the error if applicable the first step is to get your data into numpy structured array note that there are some restriction generally speaking if you know the type of property a ply file element can contain you can easily deduce the restriction for example ply file don t contain bit integer or complex data so these aren t allowed for convenience non scalar field are allowed they will be serialized a list property for example when constructing a face element if all the face are triangle a common occurrence it s okay to have a vertex index field of type i and shape instead of type object and shape however if the serialized ply file is read back in using plyfile the vertex index property will be represented a an object typed field each of whose value is an array of type i and length the reason is simply that the ply format provides no way to find out that each vertex index field ha length without actually reading all the data so plyfile ha to assume that this is a variable length property however see below and example plot py for an easy way to recover a two dimensional array from a list property for example if we wanted to create the vertex and face ply element of the tet ply data directly a numpy array for the purpose of serialization we could do a in test test py once you have suitably structured array the static method plyelement describe can then be used to create the necessary plyelement instance ornote that there s no need to create plyproperty instance explicitly this is all done behind the scene by examining some array dtype descr one slight hiccup here is that variable length field in a numpy array i e our representation of ply list property must have a type of object so the type of the list length and value in the serialized ply file can t be obtained from the array s dtype attribute alone for simplicity and predictability the length default to bit unsigned integer and the value default to bit signed integer which cover the majority of use case exception must be stated explicitly now you can instantiate plydata and serialize header comment are supported a of version obj info comment are supported a well when written they will be placed after regular comment after the format line comment can have leading whitespace but trailing whitespace may be stripped and should not be relied upon comment may not contain embedded newlines the ply format provides no way to assert that all the data for a given list property is of the same length yet this is a relatively common occurrence for example all the vertex index data on a face element will have length three for a triangular mesh in such case it s usually much more convenient to have the data in a two dimensional array a opposed to a one dimensional array of type object here s a pretty easy way to obtain a two dimensional array assuming we know the row length in advance a plausible code pattern is to read a ply file into a plydata instance perform some operation on it possibly modifying data and metadata in place and write the result to a new file this pattern is partially supported a of version the following in place mutation are supported modifying the name of a plyelement plyproperty or plylistproperty instance is not supported and will raise an error to rename a property of a plyelement instance you can remove the property from property rename the field in data and re add the property to property with the new name by creating a new plyproperty or plylistproperty instance note that it is always safe to create a new plyelement or plydata instance instead of modifying one in place and this is the recommended style object created by this library don t claim ownership of the other object they refer to which ha implication for both style creating new instance and modifying in place for example a single plyelement instance can be contained by multiple plydata instance but modifying that instance will then affect all of those containing plydata instance on python you will probably run into issue because sys stdout is a text mode stream and plyfile output binary data even for ascii format ply file there are a few way around this write to a named file instead on linux and some other unix like you can access stdout via the named file dev stdout use sys stdout buffer source http bug python org issue the design philosophy of plyfile can be summed up a follows for the most part ply concept map nicely to python and specifically to numpy and leveraging that ha strongly influenced the design of this package the element attribute of a plydata instance is simply a list of plyelement instance and the data attribute of a plyelement instance is a numpy array and a list property field of a ply element datum is referred to in the data attribute by a type of object with the value being another numpy array etc when applicable we favor simplicity over power or user friendliness thus list property type in plyelement describe always default to the same rather than say being obtained by looking at an array element which element what if the array ha length zero whatever default we could choose in that case could lead to subtle edge case bug if the user isn t vigilant also all input and output is done in one shot all the array must be created up front rather than being processed in a streaming fashion we aim to support all valid ply file however exactly what constitutes a valid file isn t obvious since there doesn t seem to be a single complete and consistent description of the ply format even the authoritative ply txt by greg turk ha some issue where can comment appear in the header it appears that in all the official example all comment immediately follow the format line but the language of the document neither place any such restriction nor explicitly allows comment to be placed anywhere else thus it isn t clear whether comment can appear anywhere in the header or must immediately follow the format line at least one popular reader of ply file choke on comment before the format line plyfile accepts comment anywhere in the header in input but only place them in a few limited place in output namely immediately after format and element line another ambiguity is name what string are allowed a ply element and property name plyfile accepts a input any name that doesn t contain space but this is surely too generous this may not be such a big deal though although name are theoretically arbitrary in practice the majority of ply element and property name probably come from a small finite set face x nx green etc a more serious problem is that the ply format specification appears to be inconsistent regarding the syntax of property definition in some example it us the syntaxand in others plyfile only support the former which appears to be standard de facto the specification explicitly state that line in the header must end with carriage return but this rule doesn t seem to be followed by anyone including the c language ply implementation by greg turk the author of the format here we stick to common practice and output unix style line ending with no carriage return but accept any line ending style in input file example beyond the scope of this document and the test are in the example directory copyright darsh ranjan this software is released under the term of the gnu general public license version see the file copying for detail

molfile the from smile function accepts a smile string or list of smile string a an argument and return a python dictionary with descriptor fingerprint name value a key value respectively if multiple smile string are supplied from smile return a list of dictionary the from mdl function accepts a filepath to an mdl molfile a an argument and return a list each list element is a dictionary with dictionary with descriptor fingerprint corresponding to each supplied molecule indexed a they appear in the sdf file alternatively you can have more control over padel descriptor with the command line description: parquet python is a pure python implementation currently with only read support of the parquet format it come with a script for reading parquet file and outputting the data to stdout a json or tsv without the overhead of jvm startup performance ha not yet been optimized but it s useful for debugging and quick viewing of data in file not all part of the parquet format have been implemented yet or tested e g nested data see todos below for a full list with that said parquet python is capable of reading all the data file from the parquet compatability project parquet python ha been tested on python and it depends on pythrift and optionally on python snappy for snappy compressed file please also install parquet python snappy parquet python is available via pypi and can be installed using pip install parquet the package includes the parquet command for reading python file e g parquet test parquet see parquet help for full usage parquet python currently ha two programatic interface with similar functionality to python s csv reader first it support a dictreader which return a dictionary per row second it ha a reader which return a list of value for each row both function require a file like object and support an optional column field to only read the specified column support the deprecated bitpackingfix handling of repetition level and definition levelstests for nested schema null datasupport reading of data from hdfs via snakebite and or webhdfs implement writingperformance evaluation and optimization i e how doe it compare to the c java implementation is done via pull request please include test with your change and follow pep to run the test you must install and execute tox pip install tox to run for all supported version if you want to run just for your current version execute pip install r requirement development txt and then nosetests

with a fancy printer and or a full up copy of acrobat can easily turn your small pdf into a little booklet for example print letter sized page on a single x but that assumes several thing including that the personnel know how to operate the hardware and software booklet py let you turn your pdf into a preformatted booklet to give them fewer chance to mess it up the cat py example will accept multiple input file on the command line concatenate them and output them to output pdf after adding some nonsensical metadata to the output pdf file the alter py example alters a single metadata item in a pdf and writes the result to a new pdf one difference is that since cat is creating a new pdf structure and alter is attempting to modify an existing pdf structure the pdf produced by alter and also by watermark py should be more faithful to the original except for the desired change for example the alter py navigation should be left intact whereas with cat py it will be stripped if you ever want to print something that is like a small booklet but need to be spiral bound you either have to do some fancy rearranging or just waste half your paper the print two py example program will for example make two side by side copy each page of of your pdf on a each output sheet but every other page is flipped so that you can print double sided and the page will line up properly and be pre collated the copy py script show a simple example of reading in a pdf and using the decodegraphics py module to try to write the same information out to a new pdf through a reportlab canvas if you done only if you really need to decodegraphics is really more than a proof of concept than anything else for most case just use the form xobject capability a shown in the example rl booklet py demo the philosophy of the library portion of pdfrw is to provide intuitive function to read manipulate and write pdf file there should be minimal leakage between abstraction layer although getting useful work done make pure functionality separation difficult a key concept supported by the library is the use of form xobjects which allow easy embedding of piece of one pdf into another addition of core support to the library is typically done carefully and thoughtfully so a not to clutter it up with too many special case there are a lot of incorrectly formatted pdfs floating around support for these is added in some case the decision is often based on what acroread and okular do with the pdfs if they can display them properly then eventually pdfrw should too if it is not too difficult or costly contribution are welcome one user ha contributed some decompression filter and the ability to process pdf stream object additional functionality that would obviously be useful includes additional decompression filter the ability to process password protected pdfs and the ability to output linearized pdfs the philosophy of the example is to provide small easily understood example that showcase pdfrw functionality in general pdf file conceptually map quite well to python the major object to think about are string most thing are string these also often decompose naturally intolists of token token can be combined to create higher level object likearrays anddictionaries andcontents stream which can be more stream of token the apparent primary difficulty in mapping pdf file to python is the indirect object provide a way to get around the chicken and egg problem of circular object reference when mapping arbitrary data structure to file to flatten out a circular reference an indirect with two special feature first an indirect attribute allows a pdfarray to be written out a an indirect pdf object second pdfrw read file lazily so pdfarray know about and resolve reference to other dictionary finally since pdfdict instance are indexed by pdfname object which always start with a and since most all standard adobe pdfname object use name formatted like camelcase it make sense to of the pdf file in addition to the tree structure pdfrw creates a special attribute named page that is a list of all the page in the document pdfrw creates the page attribute a a simplification for the user because the pdf format allows arbitrarily complicated nested dictionary to describe the page order each entry in the page list is the pdfdict object for one of the page in the file in order a you can see it is quite easy to dig down into a pdf document but what about when it s time to write it out that s all it take to create a new pdf you may still need to read the adobe pdf reference manual to figure out what need to go into the pdf but at least you don t have to sweat actually building it and getting the file offset right for the most part pdfrw try to be agnostic about the content of pdf file and support them a container but to do useful work something a little higher level is required so pdfrw work to understand a bit about the content of the container for example pdf form xobject suitable for use inside another pdf file it know enough about these to perform scaling rotation and positioning reportlab object pdfrw can recursively create a set of reportlab object from it internal object format this allows for example form xobjects to be used inside reportlab so that you can reuse content from an existing pdf file when building a new pdf with reportlab there are several example that demonstrate these feature in the example code directory even a a pure pdf container library pdfrw come up a bit short it doe not currently support most compression decompression filtersencryptionpdftk is a wonderful command line tool that can convert your pdfs to remove encryption and compression however in most case you can do a lot of useful work with pdfs without actually removing compression because only certain element inside pdfs are actually compressed pdfrw currently consists of module organized into a main package and one sub package the init py module doe the usual thing of importing a few major attribute from some of the submodules and the error py module support logging and exception generation the object sub package contains one module for each of the internal representation of the kind of basic object that exist in a pdf file with the object init py module in that package simply gathering them up and making them available to the main pdfrw package one feature that all the pdf object class have in common is the inclusion of an indirect attribute if indirect exists and evaluates to true then when the object is written out it is written out a an indirect object that is to say it is addressable in the pdf file and could be referenced by any number including zero of container object this indirect object capability save space in pdf file by allowing object such a font to be referenced from multiple page and also allows pdf file to contain internal circular reference this latter capability is used for example when each page description: what doe this mean i do not have time to fix issue myself the only way fix or new feature will be added is by people submitting pr current status voluptuous is largely feature stable there hasn t been a need to add new feature in a while but there are some bug that should be fixed why i no longer use voluptuous personally in fact i no longer regularly write python code rather than leave the project in a limbo of people filing issue and wondering why they re not being worked on i believe this notice will more clearly set expectation voluptuous despite the name is a python data validation library it is primarily intended for validating data coming into python a json yaml etc it ha three goal voluptuous now ha a mailing list send a mail to voluptuous librelist com to subscribe instruction will follow you can also contact me directly via email or twitter to file a bug create a new issue on github with a short example of how to replicate the issue the documentation is provided here see changelog md validators are simple callables no need to subclass anything just use a function error are simple exception a validator can just raise invalid msg and expect the user to get useful message schema are basic python data structure should your data be a dictionary of integer key to string int str doe what you expect list of integer float or string int float str designed from the ground up for validating more than just form nested data structure are treated in the same way a any other type need a list of dictionary consistency type in the schema are checked a type value are compared a value callables are called to validate simple twitter s user search api accepts query url like to validate this we might use a schema like this schema very succinctly and roughly describes the data required by the api and will work fine but it ha a few problem firstly it doesn t fully express the constraint of the api according to the api per page should be restricted to at most defaulting to for example to describe the semantics of the api more accurately our schema will need to be more thoroughly defined this schema fully enforces the interface defined in twitter s documentation and go a little further for completeness q is required must be a string and must be at least one character in length per page is a positive integer no greater than page is an integer schema are nested data structure consisting of dictionary list scalar and validators each node in the input schema is pattern matched against corresponding node in the input data literal in the schema are matched using normal equality check type in the schema are matched by checking if the corresponding value is an instance of the type url in the schema are matched by using urlparse library list in the schema are treated a a set of valid value each element in the schema list is compared to each value in the input data however an empty list is treated a is if you want to specify a list that can contain anything specify it a list set and frozensets are treated a a set of valid value each element in the schema set is compared to each value in the input data however an empty set set is treated a is if you want to specify a set that can contain anything specify it a set validators are simple callables that raise an invalid exception when they encounter invalid data the criterion for determining validity is entirely up to the implementation it may check that a value is a valid username with pwd getpwnam it may check that a value is of a specific type and so on the simplest kind of validator is a python function that raise valueerror when it argument is invalid conveniently many builtin python function have this property here s an example of a date validator in addition to simply determining if a value is valid validators may mutate the value into a valid form an example of this is the coerce type function which return a function that coerces it argument to the given type this example also show a common idiom where an optional human readable message can be provided this can vastly improve the usefulness of the resulting error message each key value pair in a schema dictionary is validated against each key value pair in the corresponding data dictionary by default any additional key in the data not in the schema will trigger exception this behaviour can be altered on a per schema basis to allow additional key use schema extra allow extra to remove additional key use schema extra remove extra it can also be overridden per dictionary by using the catch all marker token extra a a key by default key in the schema are not required to be in the data similarly to how extra key work this behaviour can be overridden per schema and per key with the marker token required key if a schema ha required true key may be individually marked a optional using the marker token optional key you can use voluptuous self to define a nested schema often it come handy to have a base schema that is extended with more requirement in that case you can use schema extend to create a new schema the original schema remains unchanged each key value pair in a schema dictionary is validated against each attribute value pair in the corresponding object to allow value to be none a well use any validators must throw an invalid exception if invalid data is passed to them all other exception are treated a error in the validator and will not be caught each invalid exception ha an associated path attribute representing the path in the data structure to our currently validating value a well a an error message attribute that contains the message of the original exception this is especially useful when you want to catch invalid exception and give some feedback to the user for instance in the context of an http api the path attribute is used during error reporting but also during matching to determine whether an error should be reported to the user or if the next match should be attempted this is determined by comparing the depth of the path where the check is to the depth of the path where the error occurred if the error is more than one level deeper it is reported the upshot of this is that matching is depth first and fail fast to illustrate this here is an example schema each value in the top level list is matched depth first in order given input data of the inner list will match the first element of the schema but the literal will not match any of the element of that list this error will be reported back to the user immediately no backtracking is attempted if we pas the data the is not a list type and so will not recurse into the first element of the schema matching will continue on to the second element in the schema and succeed validation rule that involve multiple field can be implemented a custom validators it s recommended to use all to do a two pas validation the first pas checking the basic structure of the data and only after that the second pas applying your cross field validator with this structure your multi field validator will run with pre validated data from the first pas and so will not have to do it own type checking on it input the flipside is that if the first pas of validation fails your cross field validator will not run voluptuous is using pytest to also include a coverage report voluptuous is heavily inspired by validino and to a lesser extent jsonvalidator and json schema pytest voluptuous is a pytest plugin that help in using voluptuous validators in asserts i greatly prefer the light weight style promoted by these library to the complexity of library like formencode

description: this is a tool for managing a recorded version number in setuptools based python project the goal is to remove the tedious and error prone update the embedded version string step from your release process making a new release should be a easy a recording a new tag in your version control system and maybe making new tarballs versioneer provides two installation mode the classic vendored mode installs a copy of versioneer into your repository the experimental build time dependency mode is intended to allow you to skip this step and simplify the process of upgrading source tree come from a variety of place within each source tree the version identifier either a string or a number this tool is format agnostic can come from a variety of place for released software the version identifier is closely related to a vcs tag some project use tag name that include more than just the version string e g myproject instead of just in which case the tool need to strip the tag prefix to extract the version identifier for unreleased software between tag the version identifier should provide enough information to help developer recreate the same tree while also giving them an idea of roughly how old the tree is after version before version many vcs system can report a description that capture this for example git describe tag dirty always report thing like g ab dirty to indicate that the checkout is one revision past the tag ha a unique revision id of ab and is dirty it ha uncommitted change the version identifier is used for multiple purpose versioneer work by adding a special version py file into your source tree where your init py can import it this version py know how to dynamically ask the vcs tool for version information at import time version py also contains revision marker and the installation process mark version py to have this marker rewritten with a tag name during the git archive command a a result generated tarballs will contain enough information to get the proper version to allow setup py to compute a version too a versioneer py is added to the top level of your source tree next to setup py and the setup cfg that configures it this override several distutils setuptools command to compute the version when invoked and change setup py build and setup py sdist to replace version py with a small static file that contains just the generated version data see install md for detailed installation instruction code which us versioneer can learn about it version string at runtime by importing version from your main init py file and running the get version function from the outside e g in setup py you can import the top level versioneer py and run get version both function return a dictionary with different flavor of version information version a condensed version string rendered using the selected style this is the most commonly used value for the project s version string the default pep style yield string like g c or g c dirty see the style section below for alternative style full revisionid detailed revision identifier for git this is the full sha commit id e g c a d cfc f fe aa c c ac date date and time of the latest head commit for git it is the commit date in iso format this will be none if the date is not available dirty a boolean true if the tree ha uncommitted change note that this is only accurate if run in a vcs checkout otherwise it is likely to be false or none error if the version string could not be computed this will be set to a string describing the problem otherwise it will be none it may be useful to throw an exception in setup py if this is set to avoid e g creating tarballs with a version string of unknown some variant are more useful than others including full revisionid in a bug report should allow developer to reconstruct the exact code being tested or indicate the presence of local change that should be shared with the developer version is suitable for display in an about box or a cli version output it can be easily compared against release note and list of bug fixed in various release the installer add the following text to your init py to place a basic version in yourproject version the setup cfg style configuration control how the vcs information is rendered into a version string the default style pep produce a pep compliant string equal to the un prefixed tag name for actual release and containing an additional local version section with more detail for in between build for git this is tag distance ghex dirty using information from git describe tag dirty always for example g c dirty indicates that the tree is like the c commit but ha uncommitted change dirty and that this commit is two revision beyond the tag for released software exactly equal to a known tag the identifier will only contain the stripped tag e g other style are available see detail md in the versioneer source tree for description versioneer try to avoid fatal error if something go wrong it will tend to return a version of unknown to investigate the problem run setup py version which will run the version lookup code in a verbose mode and will display the full content of get version including the error string which may help identify what went wrong some situation are known to cause problem for versioneer this detail the most significant one more can be found on github issue page versioneer ha limited support for source tree in which setup py is not in the root directory e g setup py and git are not sibling the are two common reason why setup py might not be in the root versioneer will look for git in parent directory and most operation should get the right version string however pip and setuptools have bug and implementation detail which frequently cause pip install from a subproject directory to fail to find a correct version string so it usually default to unknown pip install editable should work correctly setup py install might work too pip is known to have this problem but hopefully it will get fixed in some later version bug is tracking this issue the discussion in pr describes the issue from the versioneer side in more detail pip pr and pip pr contain work to improve pip to let versioneer work correctly versioneer and earlier only looked for a git directory next to the setup cfg so subprojects were completely unsupported with those release setup py develop and pip install editable allow you to install a project into a virtualenv once then continue editing the source code and test without re installing after every change entry point script setup entry point console script are a convenient way to specify executable script that should be installed along with the python package these both work a expected when using modern setuptools when using setuptools or earlier however certain operation will cause pkg resource distributionnotfound error when running the entrypoint script which must be resolved by re installing the package this happens when the install happens with one version then the egg info data is regenerated while a different version is checked out many setup py command cause egg info to be rebuilt including sdist wheel and installing into a different virtualenv so this can be surprising bug describes this one but upgrading to a newer version of setuptools should probably resolve it to upgrade your project to a new release of versioneer do the following this tool is designed to make it easily extended to other version control system all vcs specific component are in separate directory like src git the top level versioneer py script is assembled from these component by running make versioneer py in the future make versioneer py will take a vcs name a an argument and will construct a version of versioneer py that is specific to the given vcs it might also take the configuration argument that are currently provided manually during installation by editing setup py alternatively it might go the other direction and include code from all supported vcs system reducing the number of intermediate script to make versioneer easier to embed all it code is dedicated to the public domain the version py that it creates is also in the public domain specifically both are released under the unlicense a described in http unlicense org

the other is gentl the genapi module give you a way to control genicam feature of the target device support on the other hand the gentl module give you a way to control functionality that the target gentl producer support in this section you will learn how to use the genapi module first you create a node map object instantiating the nodemap class and then load a device description file on the node map object the nodemap object support several way to make it one is to load the file content a a str object another way is to load the file a an xml file the other way is to load the file a a zip file once you loaded a device description file on a node map object you would start to control genicam feature node to control the target device now assume that we are going to control a genicam feature node called foo to get the value of foo we code a follows on the other hand if foo is an integer node then we code a follows to set a value if foo is a boolean node then you code a follows or if foo is an enumeration node then you code a follows it also work for a case where foo is a string node if foo is a command node then you can execute the command with the following code in this section you will learn how to use the gentl module to be documented there is a sister project of the genicam python binding it s called harvester and is a reference implementation of the genicam python binding harvester give you an intuitive way for image acquisition to make your life easier harvester is distributed under the apache version license so you can use it for free however note that genicam applies for another license the source code can be found at github in addition haveseter is also uploaded to pypi repository so you can install that executing the following pip command in the emva website you can get useful resource to learn and use genicam standard and it compliant device and software it would be worth knowing the following keywords genapi gentl sfnc gentl sfnc clprotocol pfnc and gencp

other manually installed not installed via pip version of opencv installed e g cv module in the root of python s site package remove it before installation to avoid conflict make sure that your pip version is up to date is the minimum supported version pip install upgrade pip check version with pip v for example linux distribution ship usually with very old pip version which cause a lot of unexpected problem especially with the manylinux format select the correct package for your environment there are four different package see option and below and you should select only one of them do not install multiple different package in the same environment there is no plugin architecture all the package use the same namespace cv if you installed multiple different package in the same environment uninstall them all with pip uninstall and reinstall only one package a package for standard desktop environment window macos almost any gnu linux distribution b package for server headless environment such a docker cloud environment etc no gui library dependenciesthese package are smaller than the two other package above because they do not contain any gui functionality not compiled with qt other gui component this mean that the package avoid a heavy dependency chain to x library and you will have for example smaller docker image a a result you should always use these package if you do not use cv imshow et al or you are using some other package such a pyqt than opencv to create your gui import the package import cv all package contain haar cascade file cv data haarcascades can be used a a shortcut to the data folder for example cv cascadeclassifier cv data haarcascades haarcascade frontalface default xml read opencv documentationbefore opening a new issue read the faq below and have a look at the other issue which are already open q do i need to install also opencv separately a no the package are special wheel binary package and they already contain statically built opencv binary q pip install fails with modulenotfounderror no module named skbuild since opencv python version manylinux wheel were replaced by manylinux wheel if your pip is too old it will try to use the new source distribution introduced in to manually build opencv because it doe not know how to install manylinux wheel however source build will also fail because of too old pip because it doe not understand build dependency in pyproject toml to use the new manylinux pre built wheel or to build from source your pip version must be please upgrade pip with pip install upgrade pip q import fails on window importerror dll load failed the specified module could not be found a if the import fails on window make sure you have visual c redistributable installed if you are using older window version than window and latest system update are not installed universal c runtime might be also required window n and kn edition do not include medium feature pack which is required by opencv if you are using window n or kn edition please install also window medium feature pack if you have window server medium dlls are probably missing too please install the feature called medium foundation in the server manager beware some post advise to install window server essential medium pack but this one requires the window server essential experience role and this role will deeply affect your window server configuration by enforcing active directory integration etc so just installing the medium foundation should be a safer choice if the above doe not help check if you are using anaconda old anaconda version have a bug which cause the error see this issue for a manual fix if you still encounter the error after you have checked all the previous solution download dependency and open the cv pyd located usually at c user username appdata local program python pythonxx lib site package cv file with it to debug missing dll issue q i have some other import error a make sure you have removed old manual installation of opencv python binding cv so or cv pyd in site package q function foo or method bar return wrong result throw exception or crash interpreter what should i do a the repository contains only opencv python package build script but not opencv itself python binding for opencv are developed in official opencv repository and it s the best place to report issue also please check opencv wiki http github com opencv opencv wiki and the official opencv forum before file new bug q why the package do not include non free algorithm a non free algorithm such a surf are not included in these package because they are patented non free and therefore cannot be distributed a built binary note that sift is included in the build due to patent expiration since opencv version and see this issue for more info http github com skvark opencv python issue q why the package and import are different opencv python v cv a it s easier for user to understand opencv python than cv and it make it easier to find the package with search engine cv old interface in old opencv version wa named a cv is the name that opencv developer chose when they created the binding generator this is kept a the import name to be consistent with different kind of tutorial around the internet changing the import name or behaviour would be also confusing to experienced user who are accustomed to the import cv the aim of this repository is to provide mean to package each new opencv release for the most used python version and platform the project is structured like a normal python package with a standard setup py file the build process for a single entry in the build matrix is a follows see for example github workflow build wheel linux yml file in linux and macos build get opencv s optional c dependency on slow system such a raspberry pi the full build may take several hour on a core ryzen x the build take about minute opencv python package script in this repository is available under mit description: prompt toolkit is a library for building powerful interactive command line application in python read the documentation on readthedocs please notice that this branch is the prompt toolkit branch for most user it should be compatible with prompt toolkit but it requires at least python on the plus side prompt toolkit is completely type annotated and us asyncio natively ptpython is an interactive python shell build on top of prompt toolkit more examplesprompt toolkit could be a replacement for gnu readline but it can be much more than that some feature pure python syntax highlighting of the input while typing for instance with a pygments lexer multi line input editing advanced code completion both emacs and vi key binding similar to readline even some advanced vi functionality like named register and digraph reverse and forward incremental search work well with unicode double width character chinese input selecting text for copy paste both emacs and vi style support for bracketed paste mouse support for cursor positioning and scrolling auto suggestion like fish shell multiple input buffer no global state lightweight the only dependency are pygments and wcwidth run on linux o x freebsd openbsd and window system and much more feel free to create ticket for bug and feature request and create pull request if you have nice patch that you would like to share with others for conda do prompt toolkit is cross platform and everything that you build on top should run fine on both unix and window system window support is best on recent window build for which the command line window support vt escape sequence if not supported we fall back to using win apis for color and cursor movement it s worth noting that the implementation is a best effort of what is possible both unix and window terminal have their limitation but in general the unix experience will still be a little better for window it s recommended to use either cmder or conemu the most simple example of the library would look like this for more complex example have a look in the example directory all example are chosen to demonstrate only one thing also don t be afraid to look at the source code the implementation of the prompt function could be a good start the source code of prompt toolkit should be readable concise and efficient we prefer short function focusing each on one task and for which the input and output type are clearly specified we mostly prefer composition over inheritance because inheritance can result in too much functionality in the same object we prefer immutable object where possible object don t change after initialization reusability is important we absolutely refrain from having a changing global state it should be possible to have multiple independent instance of the same code in the same process the architecture should be layered the lower level operate on primitive operation and data structure giving when correctly combined all the possible flexibility while at the higher level there should be a simpler api ready to use and sufficient for most use case thinking about algorithm and efficiency is important but avoid premature optimization pygments syntax highlighter wcwidth determine column needed for a wide character

description: an open source python library and command line tool for classifying bird specie from flight call in audio recording birdvoxclassify is a pre trained deep learning system for classifying bird specie from flight call in short audio recording it relies on per channel energy normalization pcen for improved robustness to background noise it is made available both a a python library and a a command line tool for window o x and linux the code used to train these model can be found at this repository currently we support python and birdvoxclassify depends on the pysoundfile module to load audio file which itself depends on the non python library libsndfile on window and mac o x these will be installed automatically via the pip package manager and you can therefore skip this step however on linux libsndfile must be installed manually via your platform s package manager for debian based distribution such a ubuntu this can be done by simply runningfor more detailed information please consult the installation instruction of pysoundfile we have dropped support for tensorflow x and have moved to tensorflow x the simplest way to install birdvoxclassify is by using pip which will also install the additional required dependency if needed to install the latest version of birdvoxclassify from source clone or pull the latest version install using pip to handle python dependency aurora cramer new york university auroracramer on github for more information on the birdvox project please visit our website http wp nyu edu birdvoxsee the birdvox google group for question and relevant discussion regarding birdvox research and tool please cite the following paper when using birdvoxclassify in your work chirping up the right tree incorporating biological taxonomy into deep bioacoustic classifier jason cramer vincent lostanlen andrew farnsworth justin salamon and juan pablo bello in ieee international conference on acoustic speech and signal processing icassp barcelona spain may

the unicode standard many of it companion unicode technical standard and much of unicode cldr the pyicu source code is hosted at http gitlab pyicu org main pyicu the icu homepage is http icu unicode org see also the cldr homepage at http cldr unicode org pyicu is a python extension implemented in c that wrap the c c icu library it is known to also work a a pypy extension unless pkg config and the icu library and header are already installed building pyicu from the source on pypi involves more than just a pip call many operating system distribute pre built binary package of icu and pyicu see below mac o xensure icu is installed and can be found by pkg config a icu config wa deprecated a of icu either by following icu build instruction or by using homebrew install pyicu with the same c compiler a your python distribution more info icu and pyicu binary are both available via macports a well the same limitation about mixing binary may apply debianubuntu similar to debian there is a pyicu package available via apt alpine linux there is a pyicu package available via apk netbsd there is a pyicu package available via pkg add openbsd there is a pyicu package available via pkg add other operating system see below please refer to next section for building python icu and pyicu from source the current section is about building only pyicu from source with all dependency such a python and icu already present before building pyicu the icu library must be built and installed refer to each system s instruction for more information pyicu is built from source with setuptools or with build and pip verify that pkg config is available the icu config program is deprecated a of icu if this command return an error or doesn t return the path expected then ensure that the includes lflags cflags and library dictionary in setup py contain correct value for your platform starting with icu std c must appear in your cflags or be the default for your c compiler either build and install pyicu with setuptoolsor build pyicu with build and install it with pipeither test pyicu with setuptoolsor test pyicu with pytestthe instruction at note contain the complete step for building everything from source into a self contained directory without modifying any system directory they were made and tested on an m mac but they can be modified and reused for any unix environment in particular they outline how to build pyicu from source without icu config or pkg config being present mac o x make sure that dyld library path contains path to the directory y containing the icu libs linux solaris make sure that ld library path contains path to the directory y containing the icu libs or that you added the corresponding rpath argument to lflags window make sure that path contains path to the directory y containing the icu dlls see the change file for an up to date log of change and addition there is no api documentation for pyicu the api for icu is documented at http unicode org github io icu doc apidoc released icu c and the following pattern can be used to translate from the c apis to the corresponding python apis the icu string type unicodestring is a type pointing at a mutable array of uchar unicode bit wide character and is described here the python str type is described here and here the python unicode type is described here because of their difference icu s and python s string object are not merged into the same type when crossing the c boundary but converted icu apis taking unicodestring argument have been overloaded to also accept argument that are python str or python unicode object python str object are auto decoded into icu string using the utf encoding to convert a python byte or a python str object encoded in an encoding other than utf to an icu unicodestring use the unicodestring str encodingname constructor icu s c apis accept and return unicodestring argument in several way by value by pointer or by reference when an icu c api is documented to accept a unicodestring reference parameter it is safe to assume that there are several corresponding pyicu python apis making it accessible in simpler way for example the unicodestring locale getdisplayname unicodestring api documented here can be invoked from python in several way the icu waythe python waya unicodestring object wa allocated and converted to a python str object a unicodestring can be converted to a python unicode string with python s str or python s unicode constructor the usual len comparison and operator are all available with the additional twist that slicing is not read only and that is also available since a unicodestring is mutable for example the c icu library doe not use c exception to report error icu c apis return error via a uerrorcode reference argument all such apis are wrapped by python apis that omit this argument and throw an icuerror python exception instead the same is true for icu apis taking both a parseerror and a uerrorcode they are both to be omitted for example the unicodestring dateformat format const formattable unicodestring fieldposition uerrorcode api documented here is invoked from python with of course the simpler unicodestring dateformat format udate unicodestring documented here can be used too icu us a double floating point type called udate that represents the number of millisecond elapsed since jan utc for date in python the value returned by the time module s time function is the number of second since jan utc because of this difference floating point value are multiplied by when passed to apis taking udate and divided by when returned a udate python s datetime object with or without timezone information can also be used with apis taking udate argument the datetime object get converted to udate when crossing into the c layer many icu api take array argument a list of element of the array element type is to be passed from python an icu stringenumeration ha three next method next which return str object unext which return str object in python or unicode object in python and snext which return unicodestring object any of these method can be used a an iterator using the python built in iter function for example let e be a stringenumeration instance the icu timezone type may be wrapped with an icutzinfo type for usage with python s datetime type for example or even simpler to get the default time zone use to get the time zone s id use the tzid attribute or coerce the time zone to a string the unit test have more example of actual pyicu usage there are also a few sample ported from icu c c

description: callable pip provides a drop in replacement for pip main and support for monkey patching pip main via a known dangerous method pip main ha never been a publicly supported api for pip but it ha often been used a such this tiny package is meant to cover the gap and ease people s transition to new usage this usage is always guaranteed to work on any supported python version with any functioning version of pip instead of pip main use this method instead if you are writing a python program you can just use callable pip main yourself this is the only guaranteed safe usage callable pip provides a patch which add pip main back to pip but which is dangerous and known not to work on some version of pip if you have dependency which use pip main you can call callable pip dangerous patch yourself and it will usually work dangerous patch is so named because it is not guaranteed to work on all pip version and it is dangerous avoid it when possible you may be a consumer of package which use pip main in a context where you cannot modify or do not own any of the source these technique may help you more detail on sitecustomize py and pth file can be found in the python documentation http doc python org library site htmlremember to remove these patch if you uninstall callable pip or python will fail to start sitecustomize py can exist anywhere in the pythonpath including the directory where python is invoked add a sitecustomize py with the following content or append it to an existing sitecustomize py the pth file can have any name you want but must be installed in the site package directory it may therefore require root or other elevated privilege to add add a file e g callable pip pth with the following content all documentation is in this readme doc submit all bug report and issue here http github com sirosen callable pip issue

description: pysnooper is a poor man s debugger if you ve used bash it s like set x for python except it s fancier your story you re trying to figure out why your python code isn t doing what you think it should be doing you d love to use a full fledged debugger with breakpoints and watch but you can t be bothered to set one up right now you want to know which line are running and which aren t and what the value of the local variable are most people would use print line in strategic location some of them showing the value of variable pysnooper let you do the same except instead of carefully crafting the right print line you just add one decorator line to the function you re interested in you ll get a play by play log of your function including which line ran and when and exactly when local variable were changed what make pysnooper stand out from all other code intelligence tool you can use it in your shitty sprawling enterprise codebase without having to do any setup just slap the decorator on a shown below and redirect the output to a dedicated log file by specifying it path a the first argument we re writing a function that convert a number to binary by returning a list of bit let s snoop on it by adding the pysnooper snoop decorator the output to stderr is or if you don t want to trace an entire function you can wrap the relevant part in a with block which output something like if stderr is not easily accessible for you you can redirect the output to a file you can also pas a stream or a callable instead and they ll be used see value of some expression that aren t local variable show snoop line for function that your function call see advanced usage for more option the best way to install pysnooper is with pip conda with conda forge channel arch linux fedora linux copyright c ram rachum and collaborator released under the mit license hacker news thread and r python reddit thread april

description: pxcustodiancustodian is a simple robust and flexible just in time jit job management framework written in python using custodian you can create wrapper that perform error checking job management and error recovery it ha a simple plugin framework that allows you to develop specific job management workflow for different application error recovery is an important aspect of many high throughput project that generate data on a large scale when you are running on the order of hundred of thousand of job even an error rate of would mean thousand of errored job that would be impossible to deal with on a case by case basis the specific use case for custodian is for long running job with potentially random error for example there may be a script that take several day to run on a server with a chance of some io error causing the job to fail using custodian one can develop a mechanism to gracefully recover from the error and restart the job with modified parameter if necessary the current version of custodian also come with several sub package for error handling for vienna ab initio simulation package vasp nwchem qchem feff lobster and cp k calculation the version at the python package index pypi is always the latest stable release that will be hopefully be relatively bug free install a follows some plugins e g vasp management require additional setup please see pymatgen s documentation the bleeding edge developmental version is at the custodian s github repo the developmental version is likely to be more buggy but may contain new feature the github version include test file a well for complete unit testing after cloning the source you can type or to install the package in developmental mode custodian support python there are no other required dependency however if you wish to use many of the built in error handler and job for vasp nwchem qchem etc you will likely need pymatgen to be install a well please refer to the official custodian doc for detail scikit learn kera xgboost etc the main module of nyoka is nyoka to use it for your model you need to import the specific exporter from nyoka a the workflow is a follows for example a decision tree classifier with standardscaler create scikit learn s pipeline object and populate it with any pre processing step and the model object call pipeline fit x y method to train the model use the specific description: pyfunctional make creating data pipeline easy by using chained functional operator here are a few example of what it can do pyfunctional s api take inspiration from scala collection apache spark rdds and microsoft linq pyfunctional is available on pypi and can be installed by running then in python run from functional import seqpyfunctional is useful for many task and can natively open several common file type here are a few example of what you can do pyfunctional ha three type of function in the expression seq map lambda x x reduce lambda x y x y seq is the stream map is the transformation and reduce is the action the account transaction example could be done easily in pure python using list comprehension to show some of the thing pyfunctional excels at take a look at a couple of word count example in the next example we have chat log formatted in json line jsonl which contain message and metadata a typical jsonl file will have one valid json on each line of a file below are a few line out of example chat log jsonl next let continue that example but introduce a json database of user from example user json in the previous example we showed how pyfunctional can do word count in the next example let show how pyfunctional can join different data source in example camping purchase csv there are a list of camping purchase let do some cost analysis and compare it the required camping gear list stored in example gear list txt in addition to the aggregate function shown above sum and max by there are many more similarly there are several more set like function in addition to difference pyfunctional can read and write to sqlite database file in the example below user are read from example user db which store them a row with column id int and name string writing to a sqlite database is similarly easyjust a pyfunctional can read from csv json jsonl sqlite and text file it can also write them for complete api documentation see the collection api table or the official doc pyfunctional will auto detect file compressed with gzip lzma xz and bz this is done by examining the first several byte of the file to determine if it is compressed so therefore requires no code change to work to write compressed file every to function ha a parameter compression which can be set to the default none for no compression gzip or gz for gzip compression lzma or xz for lzma compression and bz for bz compression the only change required to enable parallelism is to import from functional import pseq instead of from functional import seq and use pseq where you would use seq the following operation are run in parallel with more to be implemented in a future release parallelization us python multiprocessing and squash chain of embarrassingly parallel operation to reduce overhead cost for example a sequence of map and filter would be executed all at once rather than in multiple loop using multiprocessingshortform documentation is below and full documentation is at doc pyfunctional org all of pyfunctional stream can be accessed through the seq object the primary way to create a stream is by calling seq with an iterable the seq callable is smart and is able to accept multiple type of parameter a shown in the example below seq also provides entry to other stream a attribute function a shown below for more information on the parameter that these function can take reference the stream documentationbelow is the complete list of function which can be called on a stream object from seq for complete documentation reference transformation and action api whenever possible pyfunctional will compute lazily this is accomplished by tracking the list of transformation that have been applied to the sequence and only evaluating them when an action is called in pyfunctional this is called tracking lineage this is also responsible for the ability for pyfunctional to cache result of computation to prevent expensive re computation this is predominantly done to preserve sensible behavior and used sparingly for example calling size will cache the underlying sequence if this wa not done and the input wa an iterator then further call would operate on an expired iterator since it wa used to compute the length similarly repr also cache since it is most often used during interactive session where it undesirable to keep recomputing the same value below are some example of inspecting lineage file are given special treatment if opened through the seq open and related apis functional util reusablefile implement a
