for what work well and what could be improved to contribute create a fork of pyfunctional make your change then make sure that they pas in order to be merged all pull request must gitter for chatchangelogto learn more about me the author visit my webpage at pedro ai i created pyfunctional while using python extensivel and finding that i missed the ease of use for manipulating data that spark rdds and scala collection have the project take the best idea from these apis a well a linq to provide an easy way to manipulate data when using scala is not an option or pyspark is overkill these people have generously contributed their time to improving pyfunctional

description: logic relational programming in python with minikanren using pip using conda first obtain the project source install the development dependency set up pre commit hook test can be run with the provided makefile logic programming is a general programming paradigm this implementation however came about specifically to serve a an algorithmic core for computer algebra system in python and for the automated generation and optimization of numeric software domain specific language code generation and compiler have recently been a hot topic in the scientific python community kanren aim to be a low level core for these project these point along with kanren example are covered in the paper minikanren a a tool for symbolic computation in python kanren enables one to express sophisticated relation in the form of goal and generate value that satisfy the relation the following code is the hello world of logic programming it asks for value of the logic variable x such that x multiple logic variable and goal can be used simultaneously the following code asks for one list containing the value of x and z such that x z and z kanren us unification to match form within expression tree the following code asks for value of x such that x the above example use eq a goal constructor that creates a goal for unification between two object other goal constructor such a membero item coll express more sophisticated relation and are often constructed from simpler one like eq more specifically membero state that item is a member of the collection coll the following example us membero to ask for all value of x such that x is a member of and x is a member of the example above made implicit use of the goal constructor lall and lany which represent goal conjunction and disjunction respectively many useful relation can be expressed with lall lany and eq alone but in kanren it s also easy to leverage the host language and explicitly create any relation expressible in python kanren store data a fact that state relationship between term the following code creates a parent relationship and us it to state fact about who is a parent of whom within the simpson family we can use intermediate variable for more complex query for instance who is bart s grandfather we can express the grandfather relationship a a distinct relation by creating a goal constructor kanren provides a fully functional constraint system that allows one to restrict unification and object type kanren come with support for relational graph operation suitable for basic symbolic algebra operation see the example in doc graph md kanren us multipledispatch and the logical unification library to support pattern matching on user defined type essentially type that can be unified can be used with most kanren goal see the logical unification project s example for demonstration of how arbitrary type can be made unifiable this project is a fork of logpy

description: starlette exporter collect basic metric for starlette and fastapi based application metric include label for the http method the path and the response status code use the http handler handle metric at path metric to expose a metric endpoint to prometheus app name set the value of the app name label for exported metric default starlette prefix set the prefix of the exported metric name default starlette label optional dict containing default label that will be added to all metric the value can be either a static value or a callback function that retrieves a value from the request object see below for example group path setting this to true will populate the path label using named parameter if any in the router path e g api v item item id this will group request together by endpoint regardless of the value of item id this option may come with a performance hit for larger router default is false which will result in separate metric for different url e g api v item api v item etc filter unhandled path setting this to true will cause the middleware to ignore request with unhandled path in other word error this help prevent filling up the metric with error and or intentially bad request default is false bucket accepts an optional list of number to use a histogram bucket the default value is none which will cause the library to fall back on the prometheus default currently skip path accepts an optional list of path that will not collect metric the default value is none which will cause the library to collect metric on every requested path this option is useful to avoid collecting metric on health check readiness or liveness probe endpoint always use int status accepts a boolean the default value is false if set to true the libary will attempt to convert the status code value to an integer if the conversion fails it will log a warning and use the initial value this is useful if you use http httstatus in your code but want your metric to emit only a integer status code optional metric a list of pre defined metric that can be optionally added to the default metric the following optional metric are available for optional metric example see below full example the included metric have built in default label such a app name method path and status code additional default label can be added by passing a dictionary to the label arg to prometheusmiddleware each label s value can be either a static value or optionally a callback function the built in default label name are reserved and cannot be reused if a callback function is used it will receive the request instance a it argument ensure that label name follow prometheus naming convention and that label value are constrained see this writeup from grafana on cardinality from header key string allowed value optional iterable a convenience function for using a header value a a label allowed value allows you to supply a list of allowed value if supplied header value not in the list will result in an empty string being returned this allows you to constrain the label value reducing the risk of excessive cardinality do not use header that could contain unconstrained value e g user id or user supplied value optional metric are pre defined metric that can be added to the default metric starlette exporter will export all the prometheus metric from the process so custom metric can be created by using the prometheus client api the new metric will now be included in the the metric endpoint output running starlette exporter in a multiprocess deployment e g with gunicorn will need the prometheus multiproc dir env variable set a well a extra gunicorn config for more information see the prometheus python client documentation this package support python code released under the apache license version http github com prometheus client pythonhttps github com encode starlettestarlette http github com encode starlettefastapi http github com tiangolo fastapiflask exporter http github com rycus prometheus flask exporteralternate starlette exporter http github com perdy starlette prometheus

coming in issue py test fixture support is documented in issue this section left intentionally blank the parameterized and parameterized expand decorator accept a list or iterable of tuples or param or a callable which return a list or iterable note that when using an iterator or a generator all the item will be loaded into memory before the start of the test run we do this explicitly to ensure that generator are exhausted exactly once in multi process or multi threaded testing environment the parameterized decorator can be used test class method and standalone function and parameterized expand can be used to generate test method in situation where test generator cannot be used for example when the test class is a subclass of unittest testcase will create the test case note that parameterized expand work by creating new method on the test class if the first parameter is a string that string will be added to the end of the method name for example the test case above will generate the method test add and and test add and the name of the test case generated by parameterized expand can be customized using the name func keyword argument the value should be a function which accepts three argument testcase func param num and params and it should return the name of the test case testcase func will be the function to be tested param num will be the index of the test case parameter in the list of parameter and param an instance of param will be the parameter which will be used will create the test case the param helper class store the parameter for one specific test case it can be used to pas keyword argument to test case if test case have a docstring the parameter for that test case will be appended to the first line of the docstring this behavior can be controlled with the doc func argument finally parameterized class parameterizes an entire class using either a list of attribute or a list of dicts that will be applied to the class the parameterized class decorator accepts a class name func argument which control the name of the parameterized class generated by parameterized class if a test function only accepts one parameter and the value is not iterable then it is possible to supply a list of value without wrapping each one in a tuple note however that if the single parameter is iterable such a a list or tuple then it must be wrapped in a tuple list or the param helper note also that python requires single element tuples to be defined with a trailing comma foo parameterized can be used with mock patch but the argument ordering can be confusing the mock patch decorator must come below the parameterized and the mocked parameter must come last note the same hold true when using parameterized expand to migrate a codebase from nose parameterized to parameterized update your requirement file replacing nose parameterized with parameterized replace all reference to nose parameterized with parameterized you re done originally only nose wa supported but now everything is supported and it only made sense to change the name there are small caveates with py test and unittest py test doe not show the parameter value ex it will show test add instead of test add and unittest unittest do not support test generator so parameterized expand must be used because spelling is difficult also parameterized doesn t require you to repeat argument name and using param it support optional keyword argument you ve likely installed the parametrized note the missing e package use parameterized with the e instead and you ll be all set

description: this is a simple python extension that let you share numpy array with other process on the same computer it us either shared file or posix shared memory a data store and therefore should work on most operating system here s a simple example to give an idea of how it work this example doe everything from a single python interpreter for the sake of clarity but the real point is to share array between python interpreter this function creates an array in shared memory and return a numpy array that us the shared memory a data backend the shared memory is identified by name which can use the file prefix to indicate that the data backend will be a file or shm to indicate that the data backend shall be a posix shared memory object for backward compatibility shm is assumed when no prefix is given most operating system implement strong file caching so using a file a a data backend won t usually affect performance the shape and dtype argument are identical to those of the numpy function numpy zero and the returned array is indeed initialized to zero the content of the array life in shared memory and or in a file and won t be lost when the numpy array is deleted nor when the python interpreter exit to delete a shared array and reclaim system resource use the sharedarray delete function this function attache a previously created array in shared memory identified by name which can use the file prefix to indicate that the array is stored a a file or shm to indicate that the array is stored a a posix shared memory object for backward compatibility shm is assumed when no prefix is given the optional parameter ro indicates that the array shall be attached read only an array may be simultaneously attached from multiple different process i e python interpreter the content of the array life in shared memory and or in a file and won t be lost when the numpy array is deleted nor when the python interpreter exit to delete a shared array reclaim system resource use the sharedarray delete function this function destroys the previously created array identified by name which can use the file prefix to indicate that the array is stored a a file or shm to indicate that the array is stored a a posix shared memory object for backward compatibility shm is assumed when no prefix is givenafter calling delete the array will not be attachable anymore but existing attachment will remain valid until they are themselves destroyed the data is reclaimed by the system when the very last attachment is deleted this function return a list of previously created array stored a posix shm object along with their name data type and dimension this function only work on linux because it directly access file exposed under dev shm there doesn t seem to be a portable method of achieving this flag for the msync method of the base object of the returned numpy array see below specifies that an update be scheduled but the call return immediately flag for the msync method of the base object of the returned numpy array see below request an update and wait for it to complete flag for the msync method of the base object of the returned numpy array see below asks to invalidate other mapping of the same file so that they can be updated with the fresh value just written sharedarray register it own python object a the base object of the returned numpy array this base object expose the following method and attribute this method is a wrapper around msync and is only useful when using file backed array i e not posix shared memory msync flush the mapped memory region back to the filesystem the flag are exported a constant in the module definition see above and are a map of the msync flag please refer to the manual page of msync for detail this method is a wrapper around mlock lock the memory map into ram preventing that memory from being paged to the swap area this method is a wrapper around munlock unlock the memory map allowing that memory to be paged to the swap area this constant string is the name of the array a passed to sharedarray create or sharedarray attach it may be passed to sharedarray delete base address of the array in memory size of the array in memory python or numpy posix shared memory interfacesharedarray us the posix shm interface shm open and shm unlink and so should work on most posix operating system linux bsd etc it ha been reported to work on macos and it is unlikely to work on window the extension us the distutils python package that should be familiar to most python user to test the extension directly from the source tree without installing type to build and install the extension system wide type the package is also available on pypi and can be installed using the pip tool a few people have reported segfaults with very large array using posix shared memory this is not a bug in sharedarray but rather an indication that the system ran out of posix shared memory on linux a tmpfs virtual filesystem is used to provide posix shared memory and by default it is given only about of the total available memory depending on the distribution that amount can be changed by re mounting the tmpfs filesystem with the size option also you can make the change permanent on next boot by setting shm size in etc default tmpfs on recent debian installation sharedarray us one memory map per array that is attached or created by default the maximum number of memory map per process is set by the linux kernel to if you want to create more array than that you need to tune the kernel parameter vm max map count and set it to a higher value note that for the change to be permanent you need to add this line to etc sysctl conf since version all array are now page aligned in memory to be used with simd instruction e g fftw library a a side effect array created with a previous version of sharedarray aren t compatible with the new version the location of the metadata changed save your work before upgrading this package is hosted on gitlab at http gitlab com tenzing shared arraypackages are also available on pypi at http pypi python org pypi sharedarrayfor bug report feature request suggestion patch and everything else related to sharedarray feel free to raise issue on the project page you can also contact the maintainer directly by email at mat parad x org

description: autoflake remove unused import and unused variable from python code it make use of pyflakes to do this by default autoflake only remove unused import for module that are part of the standard library other module may have side effect that make them unsafe to remove automatically removal of unused variable is also disabled by default autoflake also remove useless pas statement by default running autoflake on the below exampleresults into allow autoflake to remove additional unused import other than than those from the standard library use the import option it accepts a comma separated list of name to remove all unused import whether or not they are from the standard library use the remove all unused import option to remove unused variable use the remove unused variable option below is the full listing of option configure default argument using a pyproject toml file or a setup cfg file the name of the configuration parameter match the flag e g use the parameter expand star import for the flag expand star import to run the unit test there is also a fuzz test which run against any collection of given python file it test autoflake against the file and check how well it doe by running pyflakes on the file before and after the test fails if the pyflakes result change for the worse this is done in memory the actual file are left untouched it might be the case that you have some import for their side effect even if you are not using them directly in that file that is common for example in flask based application in where you import python module file that imported a main app to have them included in the route for example a those import are not being used directly if you are using the option remove all unused import they would be removed to prevent that without having to exclude the entire file you can add a noqa comment at the end of the line like that line will instruct autoflake to let that specific line a is add the following to your pre commit config yaml

description: ml collection is a library of python collection designed for ml use case the two class called configdict and frozenconfigdict are dict like data structure with dot access to nested element together they are supposed to be used a a main way of expressing configuration of experiment and model this document describes example usage of configdict frozenconfigdict fieldreference a frozenconfigdictis an immutable hashable type of configdict a fieldreference is useful for having multiple field use the same value it can also be used for lazy computation you can use placeholder a a shortcut to create a fieldreference field with a none default value this is useful if a program us optional configuration field note that the indirection provided by fieldreferences will be lost if accessed through a configdict using a fieldreference in a standard operation addition subtraction multiplication etc will return another fieldreference that point to the original s value you can use fieldreference get to execute the operation and get the reference s computed value and fieldreference set to change the original reference s value if a fieldreference ha none a it original value or any operation ha an argument of none then the lazy computation will evaluate to none we can also use field in a configdict in lazy computation in this case a field will only be lazily evaluated if configdict get ref is used to get it lazily computed value in a configdict can be overridden in the same way a regular value the reference to the fieldreference used for the lazy computation will be lost and all computation downstream in the reference graph will use the new value you cannot create cycle using reference fortunately the only way to create a cycle is by assigning a computed field to one that is not the result of computation this is forbidden here are some more advanced example showing lazy computation with different operator and data type you can use and eq a configdict to check equality among configdict and frozenconfigdict object equality check see if the computed value are the same equality is satisfied if two set of computation are different a long a they result in the same value here is an example with lock and deepcopy for more example take a look at ml collection config dict example for example and gotchas specifically about initializing a configdict see ml collection config dict example config dict initialization py this library add flag definition to absl flag to handle config file it doe not wrap absl flag so if using any standard flag definition alongside config file flag user must also import absl flag currently this module add two new flag type namely define config file which accepts a path to a python file that generates a configuration and define config dict which accepts a configuration directly configuration are dict like structure see configdict whose nested element can be overridden using special command line flag see the example below for more detail use ml collection config flag alongside absl flag for example script py config py now after running we get usage of define config dict is similar to define config file the main difference is the configuration is defined in script py instead of in a separate file script py config file flag are compatible with the command line flag syntax all the following option are supported for non boolean value in configuration option for boolean value are slightly different note that config boolean field value is not supported it s sometimes useful to be able to pas parameter into get config and change what is returned based on this configuration one example is if you are grid searching over parameter which have a different hierarchical structure the flag need to be present in the resulting configdict it would be possible to include the union of all possible leaf value in your configdict but this produce a confusing config result a you have to remember which parameter will actually have an effect and which won t a better system is to pas some configuration indicating which structure of configdict should be returned an example is the following config file the value of config string will be anything that is to the right of the first colon in the config file path if one exists if no colon exists no value is passed to get config producing a typeerror if description: multimethod provides a decorator for adding multiple argument dispatching to function the decorator creates a multimethod object a needed and register the function with it annotation there are several multiple dispatch library on pypi this one aim for simplicity and speed with caching of argument type it should be the fastest pure python implementation possible func is now a multimethod which will delegate to the above function when called with argument of the specified type subsequent usage will register new type and function to the existing multimethod of the same name alternatively function can be explicitly registered in the same style a functools singledispatch this syntax is also compatible with mypy which by default check that each name is defined once multimethods are implemented a mapping from signature to function and can be introspected a such multimethods support any type that satisfy the issubclass relation including abstract base class in collection abc and typing subscripted generic are supported naturally checking subscript is slower but the implementation is optimized cached and bypassed if no subscript are in use in the parameter empty iterables match any subscript but don t special case how the type are normally resolved dispatch resolution detail classmethod and staticmethod may be used with a multimethod but must be applied last i e wrapping the final multimethod definition for class and instance method cl and self participate in the dispatch a usual they may be left blank when using annotation otherwise use object a a placeholder overload dispatch on annotated predicate each predicate is checked in the reverse order of registration the implementation is separate from multimethod due to the different performance characteristic if an annotation is a type instead of a predicate it will be converted into an isinstance check multidispatch is a wrapper to provide compatibility with functools singledispatch it requires a base implementation and use of the register method instead of namespace lookup it also provisionally support dispatching on keyword argument use metaclass multimeta to create a class with a special namespace which convert callables to multimethods and register duplicate callables with the original equivalent to branch coverage

description: a library for composing asynchronous and event based program using observable collection and query operator function in pythonfor v x please go to the v branch rxpy v x run on python or above to install rxpy reactive extension for python rxpy is a set of library for composing asynchronous and event based program using observable sequence and pipable query operator in python using rx developer represent asynchronous data stream with observables query asynchronous data stream using operator and parameterize concurrency in data event stream using scheduler read the documentation to learn the principle of rxpy and get the complete reference of the available operator if you need to migrate code from rxpy v x read the migration section there is also a list of third party documentation available here join the conversation on slack the gracious folk at pyslackers have given u a home in the rxpy slack channel please join u there for question conversation and all thing related to rxpy to join navigate the page above to receive an email invite after signing up join u in the rxpy channel please follow the community guideline and term of service rxpy is a fairly complete implementation of rx with more than operator and over passing unit test rxpy is mostly a direct port of rxjs but also borrows a bit from rxnet and rxjava in term of threading and blocking operator rxpy follows pep so all function and method name are lowercase with word separated by underscore a necessary to improve readability thus net code such a need to be written with an in python with rxpy you should use named keyword argument instead of positional argument when an operator ha multiple optional argument rxpy will not try to detect which argument you are giving to the operator or not
